title: (REWORKED) Quantum || Being Forged From Two Souls

The official unofficial character mod for NULL from Tankakuka's [i]SOUL RING[/i], the work-in-progress beam-em-up that simply does and doesn't exist! Freshly reworked with a brand new, juiced up kit!

This [b]aerial fighter[/b] has both [b]bruiser and grappler attributes[/b], with its main conceit coming from its ability to [b]swap between two stances[/b] -- one which [b]decreases gravity[/b] and another which [b]increases damage[/b], and [b][u]both providing unique variants of its Special moves[/u][/b] -- and [b]sacrificing them to place as much more powerful install AoEs in the arena[/b]. Utilizing these in tandem with its ability to pressure from a safe distance using medium and long-range moves, as well as the ability to [b]teleport 60 ticks in the past at will[/b], it can command oppressive control over the space between it and its opponent.

This character also comes with a [b]Canon Playerstyle[/b] which provides an [b]unique variation for their intro animation![/b] That, plus the [b]stage mod tie-in, Limber De Koko[/b], are available in the collection listed above. Check it out!

author: Author
title: [13th Month] Kaede Mikazuki
description:
"Perfection isn't something to strive for. It is the only acceptable state of existence."

The assassin, as known as Shinigami in the underworld, with nihilistic craving for perfection. He hates excessive things, so he lives a shy life, and never unsheathes his blade more than necessary.
Kaede is a melee-focused rushdown character, who utilizes "Tsukikage" gauge, shown as the crescent moon. More Tsukikage he has, more can he unsheath his blade, unlocking stances tied to Moon Phases - Shingetsu, Mikadzuki, Jogen no Tsuki and Michirutsuki. Some people also say that he can use something called "Mangetsu", the full moon... but it must be just a town legend.
Despite being a melee rushdown, Kaede has quite a few setplay moves, especially in later stances he can unlock. As long as you have enough Tsukikage to have the stance you need, this killer is equipped with moves to fit any possible situation.
When he hits enemies by red edge of his smears (as well as when he uses his Hustle), he gains so-called "Strokes of Death", which he can spend on enhancing the moves he uses from the unsheathing stances.
This mod support Codex, so if you want to know more about specific moves, you can check it out!

Mod concept, moveset, icons, UI and code: By yours truly (Author)
Sprites and thumbnail: By TBeans

Please, be polite and precise, both in your combat and words, for these are ones of a few things Kaede likes in strangers.

author: Author
title: [Library of Babel] Oliver Clain, the Empty Husk
description:
"If even gods refuse to weep for this world, I will do it in their stead"

Formerly a renowed hero, now an empty husk of himself, Oliver is bound to obey his raging emotions.
Oliver utilizes 2 kits: Base and Hate. In Base, he is a Puppet Zoner with somewhat lower than usual damage and lower combo potential, due to all his normals not cancelling on hit. In his Hate state, however, he loses his ranged abilities and Puppet in exchange for great combo power and hyper armor... but he loses HP every tick in that state! How do you choose the state?... you don't! Oliver has Hate gauge to determine where he goes this "rage mode". It fills all the time, but you can halt it by using Hustle or Hatred with toggle off!
Some say, that if you have 3 Meter and hit opponent, while in Hate, you can finally awake from your slumber and fight... like yourself.

Go on. Maybe you cannot save the world... but at least you can save yourself.

author: Author
title: [Library of Babel] Sebastian Clain, Grief of the Griefless
description:
"Will you make me feel again?"

The son of Sol Clain and Gerda, a powerful mage and a tormented soul who wish to be at the very least, cut down.
Sebastian is one of a few dedicated zoners in YOMI Hustle. He has multiple unique mechanics:
1. He doesn't take damage. He still can be hit and enters hitstun and all. But he doesn't lose HP. Instead, he stores damage he would take as, well, "Stored Damage" (blue orb). He can accumulate it infinitely. After some time while he stores damage, he also gains "interest" (x1.0, x1.1, x1.2, x1.35).
Also, when he is hit, he loses some time based on damage he would take. When his Time reaches 0, he takes all damage he stored with interest, and replenshes his Time.
Also, if he uses Hustle, he can remove some of Stored Damage and take the rest at x0.85 "interest".
Mind that this whole gimmick only works if his Broken Timepiece Level is below 3!
2. He starts at "Broken Timepiece 1" (aka Clock Level 1). At certain Stored Damage (300), he can consume some of it to increase his Clock Level. 2nd Clock Level unlocks something I'll touch in gimmick 3. Then, at Clock Level 2, if he has 350+ Stored Damage, he can enter Clock Level 3. At Clock Level 3, 1st frame of each of his moves (not including universal moves) is cut off. So, all his moves are 1 frame faster.
3.  He can Enhance and EX-Enhance his Specials and Supers. Enhance consumes some HP (in reality, it increases Stored Damage) and makes Special/Super stronger. Different Specials and Supers consume different amount of HP. EX-Enhance consume 2 Super Meter, but makes buff stronger/adds different buff. At Clock Level 1, he can only do Enhance for Specials. At Clock Level 2, he can Enhance both Specials and Supers. At Clock Level 3, he can EX-Enhance (he can't EX-Enhance below CL3). At CL3, his Enhances consume no HP!

So, wield your powers with caution, because eventually, they will devour you whole.

author: Quinn
title: Ada
description:
Ada joins the competition, using his sword for swift maneuverability and traps.

Part of Wave 2 of the RHG Mod Pack.

Ada Owned by Cozie
RHG Mod Pack Hosted by Eminence

Noteworthy Mechanics/Gimmicks:

Wires
- Wires can be loosened from Ada's sword by using the toggle "Loosen" on neutral attacks, or through the Special move "Let Loose".
- Ada can pull towards these wires for swift movement.
- Ada can tighten his wires for dangerous setups. Once tightened, they pull back towards Ada with an active hitbox. If the opponent or their projectiles hits a wire, it will force the wires to tighten up.
- Some moves require wires to be out on the field in order to be used. These include:
- Tighten Up, Surf, Instant Reel, and Shockwave.
- Getting hit disables all of your wires.

Throwable Sword + Fists Stance
- Ada can throw his sword to extend combos or catch the opponent off guard. This will put him in "Fists Stance"
- Ada's Special moves in Fists Stance will automatically catch the sword when it's nearby him. There will also be a toggle named "Reel" that's used to tighten up the wires. These rules don't apply to the move "Found You".
- Getting hit, or using any variation of Burst will instantly return your sword to you, putting you back in Sword Stance.

Marking + Found You
- On successful hit (even on block), marks the opponent and grants access to "Found You"
- Found You is Ada's only guard break in Sword Stance. It tracks the opponent horizontally and travels full screen.
- Found You can also be accessed in Fists Stance

author: AxNoodle
title: AI Opponent | Goon
description:
An easy-to-beat AI opponent.
You can select its moves to look at its predictions, but ultimately, it locks in its own move and DI.
This is a "pilot" of sorts to test out an exceedingly simple AI-controlled character before working up to a general solution.
The character hasn't got a very diverse moveset to limit "thinking time" - it takes a 1-3 seconds to think as of now, but increased complexity may cause the number to have to rise.
On Easy and Medium, it looks one step ahead - it'll look at the moves you can make (to a limited extent) and respond accordingly.
It's not good at comboing, but it'll try its best!

Get the Mod Options mod to be able to change difficulties - the more difficult, the more time it will spend thinking.

Note on MultiHustle:
While Goon is now compatible, it is slow and resource-taxing, as simulating MultiHustle takes more memory and takes longer. It should work fine with a few bots on Easy or Medium, but don't expect a playable game with lots of Hard Mode. I do have plans to speed it up in the future, but that'll likely be specific to the general AI. This is just the pilot, after all.
If you find any bugs with MultiHustle specific to Goon, please let me know.

Short FAQ:
- How do I use the mod?
This is a character named "Goon" that is controlled by an AI. The general AI is under development and coming soon, which you'll be able to use on any character!

- Do I need to turn P2 input off?
No, and I would advise against it. You want to be able to check what options your opponent can use, after all!

- My game isn't responding after I press lock in. Has the game crashed?
No, it just needs a second. Especially on Hard Mode, it can be taxing on your computer's resources.

- What if an AI could be a boss character or do other things?
I'm also planning to make a library to aid creation of specific AIs for bosses or special characters that wouldn't fit a general purpose AI playstyle. Stay tuned!

- The mod's showing up as Null. What do I do?
This is a common issue with mods. Go into settings and Delete Character Cache.

author: Blancmache
title: Akali
description:
[b] Patch v0.5.4  05/07/2023[/b]
- Fixed Ninja QS inherited node for Akali Q & E. Probably cause some crashes to stop happening.
- Lowered Vision of Death damage & added damage scaling.
- [R] Perfect Execution costs 2 bar now, I think it didn't for awhile.
- [R] Lethal Tempo sweetspot SFX and VFX fixed. There won't be an awkward pause now.

[b] Patch v0.5.3 Hotfix 18/06/2023[/b]
- Fixed crashes happening from Official 1.5 Patch

[b] Patch v0.5.2 Hotfix 13/03/2023[/b]
- Adrift and Taunt were causing crashes, fixed.

[b] Patch v0.5.1 Hotfix 12/03/2023[/b]
- Itch.io version Playable now! Removed a robot SFX
- Kama bar correctly disappears when kama is being used now
- [R] Perfect Execution cost increased to 2 bars.
- Perfect Execution kama activation fixed now, (used to always activate kama after one hit)

[b] Patch v0.5 08/03/2023 [/b]

 [b] - [New] Fancy UI icons!  [/b]Every ability has an icon now, she feels like a real character now (UI at least)
 [b] - [New] Jaunt  [/b]- Akali does a quick teleport forward, hitting behind her. Variable range dash and hit, with long recovery. Its used for akali to maintain pressure in neutral. It has about 15 frames more during combos.
 [b] - [New] Adrift  [/b]-  Akali throws bouncing Kunais, they last only a short while for now. Replaces caltrops.
 [b] - [New] Wayfinder  [/b] - Akali redirects the bouncing kunai to target towards the enemy's location, can bounce off walls. (Targeting is a bit buggy)
 [b] - [New] Hustle  [/b]- Akali spins her kunai on her fingers, then tosses it in the air, then attempts to catch it. Spinning the kunai generates meter, catching the kunai generates even more meter. Can Substitute or Wayfinder the thrown kunai to interrupt the hustle.
- Fixed tiger knee hitbox detection, also made sweetspot harder to hit (2 ticks long from 5), hitbox is now 10 ticks long (from 5)
- Rainwater now grants more momentum if cast on the ground, this can be used to catch falling opponents better.
- Lowered Gruesome Display's multihit damage.
- Smoke grenade throw strength is lowered.
- Slightly tweaked Q Kunais hitstun and duration.
- VFX added for Smoke Explosion for Smoke Grenade, Smoke Grenade sprite recolored to be clearer.
- Akali sprites for Dropkick, will kick on active frames now.


[b]------------- MOVE LIST -------------[/b]

[b]Q[/b] - Throws 5 projectiles at limited angle, it activates your kama circle passive.

[b]W[/b] - 6 Way move, throws a smoke grenade that creates a smoke cloud. Being in the smoke cloud with your opponent gives you access to shunpo - a broken 5 tick teleport

[b]Shunpo[/b] - A toggleable teleport that teleports you to the opponent in 5 ticks if you are both in the smoke, you can input a move alongside it.

[b]E[/b] - Throws a shuriken at a direction, hitting the opponent with it forces you into a followup state that you can cancel into a homing dash.

[b]R[/b] - Quick Slash ninja but longer range and slightly slower startup, can follow up with another free R that has a sweetspot in the middle.

[b]Kama Circle passive[/b] - Leaving the circle after being hit by Q or E, grants you an empowered kama. Allowing you to cast one of two powerful moves in the super category (will add more in the future)

[b]Rainwater[/b] - Axl's Rainwater from guilty gear. Large disjointed air hitbox. Has a blindspot that is closer to Akali.

[b]KamaGroundedStrike[/b] - Grounded strike, similar to rainwater in the air, but forward and on the ground. Has a blindspot if you dash towards her.

[b]Caltrops[/b] - Ninja's Caltrops

[b]Substitution[/b] - Ninja's Substitution

[b]Tiger Knee[/b] - Smash's Captain falcon's knee. With a sweet spot that is +50 on hit

[b]Punch, Slide Kick, Airkicks, Dropkick, Stomp[/b] - is self explainatory, mostly also stolen from ninja's moveset. Punch is 1-2 ticks slower to nerf shunpo.

author: FatYoshi69
title: Assassin, Shadow of the Hollow Night
description:
He wanders -- Bound by the will and governing of an ancient family, but his emotions tremor. The promise he made with a young girl shackles him, in rusty chains he strives to sever. The Night becomes a labyrinth, impeding his progress. Will he ever find the beacon he seeks?

My first YOMI mod, Assassin is a recreation of Seth from Under Night In-Birth with a few added things and changes I thought would be cool.
Considering my track record this character will definitely release with bugs and/or dumb oversights, if you find anything broken or weird please let me know in the comments.

Notes:
- Assassin doesn't have a Hustle and instead has Concentration, which speeds up Burst build and slows down the opponent's Burst build.
- Black Hole Orb, Shredder and Moonrise are Force Functions, which are moves that cost half your Burst meter to use. You can still use them if you have less than 50% Burst though, and they'll give your opponent the amount of Burst you're missing instead.
- Chain Shift, Assassin's Whiff Cancel, costs all of your Burst but can be used in neutral with a longer animation to convert your Burst meter into Super meter.
- Veil Off is an alt burst usable starting at 5 bars, and drains all of your meter over time. During Veil Off, Assassin gains a 20% damage boost, the ability to overspend Super meter, and an IK followup from level 5 if you have 3 bars remaining and the opponent's health is low enough.
- Cross Cast Veil Off, the combo version of Veil Off, additionally costs your Burst to activate.

author: MowMeow
title: Asuka R#
description:
You can no longer skip the intro due to possible desync issues. let me know if you have problems starting online matches

Spend Mana to use spells. If you run out of Mana, you will not be able to use spells and you will take double damage. You also can't use spells that would leave you with no mana.

Bookmark: Get a Spell. They appear in the Super category. You can not use Bookmark when you already have 4 or more spells. If a new spell does not appear, that is because it is a duplicate and is stacked on top of a spell you already have.

Change Test Case: This decides the deck he will pull from when he uses Bookmark.

Recover Mana: The colored move decides what other resource to spend. The arrow decides how long the move will last (10f or until next opponent turn). The move will cancel automatically if either your Mana is full or your sacraficial resource is depleted.

Wild Assault: Lvl 1 super. +5 on block.

Roman Cancel: Slide in a direction. Blue RC takes 5 frames. Red RC has a hitbox.

High Compression Submicron Particle Sphere/Cube: Lvl 2 super. The cube will be affected by staffs, and the sphere will not.

Bookmark (Full Order): Get 3 spells from all 3 test cases, giving you 9 spells.

author: Giovanni Nero
title: Axl Low (Old)
description:
New Axl Remake: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3242612146

He might be very scuffed let me know if anything is off Because this is the first mod I've made. 
This took me like 3 or 4 weeks of constant trial and error.


[Overview]
Axl has his Gatling system from guilty gear accent core +r so certain moves wont be able to be stringed (P-K-S-H-D) but all normals are able to be canceled into supers and specials.

He also has annoying moves as well as moves that move him around in weird ways, with the caveat being that they don't do a lot of damage and mostly leaving into a knockdown, but they do open your opponent up for future combos.

Axl's main drawback is his little damage he needs to use his meter for a lot of things if you want to do big damage. Hitting your opponent with a raw super will do a lot more damage than normal as well.

A lot of his moves hit OTG so don't forget to get up of else you might allow him to put you right back into a combo.


[Moves]

-Standing Punch: A sorta slow move meant to hit people who are attacking from above. It leads into more of his nonsense in the air.

-Low Punch: Extends a sickle out to hit the opponent low multiple times. It can lead into a grab if you are close enough

-Sickle Corner: Another low that's very quick to bring out and opens up your opponent for a full combo. It also used to extend a combo and bounce people off the ground.

-Forward Kick: while his standing punch covers a specific area forward kick has Axl extend a chain diagonally again to hit areal opponents. Unlike standing punch this move can loop with his Low Slash.

-Low Kick: A fast normal that lowers Axl to the ground. It clashes with a lot of moves due to how slow it could be, However its not always reliable as a safe option.

-C. Slash: A very fast but small normal that leads into most of Axl's Combos.

-F. Slash: Not as fast as close slash but is great for keeping a combo string going.

-Low Slash: Another one of Axl's anti-air moves that could loop for a bit with Forward Kick.

-Heavy Slash: The slowest grounded normal, if you whiff with this you're getting hit, but when it hit it can leave your opponent in hit stun for a while. Also you can't lead into much with it however its good to use when you know when your opponent is going to get sent airborne.

-Forward Heavy Slash: This moves throws you into the air to hit your opponent with an over-head. It is very slow, but it is good to use when you opponent is far away and you have the momentum to fling yourself forward to catch them. The move also resets your Gatling meaning you can start a whole new combo string with it.

-Low Heavy Slash: Not a lot of range with this one, but still annoying to get hit by. The move has multiple hitboxes to it so if you use it in a combo there is a chance that you might reach the hit limit and pop your opponent into the air but due to the move not having a lot of knock-back they will be able to act right after it.

-Low Dust: On hit the move gives you a free knockdown, if you chose to act after the hit you can't use normals; only supers and specials.

-Air Punch: Very fast but low range punch in the air

-Air Forward Punch: Axl extends his chain to hit you when he is in the air. the move has multiple hit boxes

-Air Kick: Axl Gains momentum to kick his opponent when he is in the air.

-Aerial Slash: Axl extends his weapon to the ground to hit a aerial of grounded  target

-Air Heavy: When used Axl covers his upper body with a hitbox that causes his opponent to be more open to combos

-Aerial Dust: Axl dropkick you in the air


[Specials]

-Rensengeki: A mid range special which on hit could lead into a combo or a knockdown.

-Benten Gari: The fastest Special here. This move is a two part move which on hit flings the opponent into the air into a followup with your sickle that hits them again and allows them to act.

-Benten: Is Axl's other fast special this one misses the follow up and has a different property to it. The move dose not do much damage and is only really useful for getting people off of you and resenting the fight to neutral.

-Winter Mantis: The slowest Special he has. Axl Trows his chain behind his opponent to catch them and pull them closer for a close-line that gives you a knockdown if it hits. The hits that push the opponent to you do no damage.

-RainWater: Sends Axl backwards into the air to hit his opponent with a low that also brings them to you. Can lead into some goofy stuff.

-Snail: A fast move that hit people both in the air and and the ground, However if you are too close to your opponent then the move will whiff.

-Raiei Sageki: This move launches you behind you opponent to hit them with a reverse overhead. The move is slow to use however and can be beaten by dashes.

-Downward Axl Bomber: Axl sends himself diagonally to hit his opponent like a missile, the move causes your opponent to bounce off of the ground if it hits.

-Snail: Similar to the grounded variant but instead sends the target to the ground for a knockdown. The move can also bounce the opponent into the air

-Kokuu Geki: Covers a strict area around you and on hit can leave you opponent open for more attacks. The opponent can also just dash towards you to avoid the attack.


[Supers]

-Shark Strike: Cost one bar of meter to use. It hits your opponent and brings them to you.

-Axl Bomber: Cost one bar to use both on the ground and the air, the move on hit will send your opponent into the air. The move can be canceled into itself as long as you have the meter to use it.

-Baton Super (Shiranami no Homura): Cost 2 bars of meter. The move is a quick but low range 3 part super that dose decent damage. On the second hit there is a hit-box behind him that also leads into the final hit.

-Byakue Renshou: Cost 3 bars of meter. Has a very large hit box but is very slow if you just use raw. The move also dose the most damage and can wall splat.

-Time Stop: Cost 3 bars of meter. Axl freeze time. The move stops all his momentum.

author: El Pickler
title: Bard
description:
Bard is a fairly complex fighter, designed around unlocking notes by attacking his opponent to unlock more powerful attacks and songs. Due to his complexity, though not required, I recommend Degritone's Tooltips mod: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2932753033&searchtext=tooltips

Bard's Basic attacks generate Notes. By generating notes, you unlock Bard's repertoire of powerful Special attacks.

Bard has 3 Supers:
Encore repeats bard's most recent offensive song without altering his Notes.
Dal Segno stores the state of Bard's Note queue every time he clears it. By activating this Super, bard replaces his notes with those he has stored.
Grand Performance allows Bard to play 3 notes in rapid succession, playing a single note song with the first note, a 2 note song with the first and second note, and a 3 note song with all 3.

author: Thomased22
title: Belmont: Vampire Killer (Freakishly Big Balance Patch)
description:
[h1]Character Codex is extremely, highly, freakishly recommended. It's been set as a requirement so you can instantly download it with the character. But is not required for the character to be played nor is it needed for any additional functions.[/h1]

Belmont, monster assassin and warrior, powers up with collectible items and extra weapons to fill out his move set for a unique Search Action inspired playstyle! He comes with a healthy variety of melee attacks as well as many setup tools. He starts off a bit weak, but becomes a highly versatile threat when fully stocked.
 
By completing certain conditions, he can cause ammo, new weapons, and even the Belmont family crest to drop from the opponent on hit. These items must be collected by making contact with them!
 
[list]
[*]New weapons expand your moveset with a new special and a new super *each*. The family crest upgrades his primary weapon, called Vampire Killer, making it deal more damage and giving him more range.
 
[*]He also has a few martial arts attacks that are independent of all of these. As well as many free action toggles that influence his moves. By mixing and matching all of the above you can abuse his tricky monster slaying techniques to out maneuver your opponents.
 
[*]But be advised! The ultimate power of his fully leveled primary weapon is reverted if you get hit. Sending you back temporarily to it's previous form until you collect another powerup.

[*]With a game faithful moveset (sometimes down to the frame data), and even more faithful sound design (and accurately bad voice acting) Belmont is a first of his kind character. A direct port of stuff from other (non fighting) games to Yomi. With a unique Search Action inspired playstyle, risk taking and decision making are more important than ever!
 
[*]The lovingly done implementation of everything he does, done by diehard Castlevania fans; is certain to elate every single little microbe of joy that Konami refuses to these days to anyone in the know.  But even if you know jack squat, Belmont comes equipped with a very in depth codex! With the knowledge collected over a thousand years of crusading against the dark lord of Castlevania, anyone can slay the monsters lurking in custom character steam lobbies!
[/list]

So grab your magical transforming flail, a few knives, and all the love of free will and humanity you can muster! You'll need it for the challenges ahead of you.

author: bonehouse
title: Bog [v1.5]
description:
[h1][b]THE ACIDIC BLOOD CONJURER CALLS....[/b][/h1]
[b]Adds "Bog" as a playable character![/b]

[i](Bog is an original character by acb and has been featured in many RHG battles and Duels, as well as my Fatal Art games)[/i]

[b][url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/changelog/2984527750]Bog was recently updated, please check the patch notes![/url][/b]

[h1][b]A DUSKHOUSE MOD....[/b][/h1]
[i]This mod started off as an unfinished Bog mod by Dusk with completely different sprites, but the same core mechanic. I love Bog so much that and loved the work that was already done that I had to see this to completion, [/i]
[i]so Dusk and I collaborated on this together, Dusk doing most of the coding and work on Bog's Blud Bug mechanics & sprites, I mostly worked on the main animations and balacing, both of us doing the visual/audio work :)[/i]

[i]You may know Dusk from the Orchid, Susano'o and The Spot character mods![/i]
https://steamcommunity.com/id/onyanyanyan/myworkshopfiles/?appid=2212330


-------


[h1][b]NEW STAGE: BOG'S CAVE[/b][/h1]
[i]Complete the Bog mod with his own stage (as seen in the screenshots), commissioned by my favorite stage artist [url=https://steamcommunity.com/id/KoalaV3ngance/myworkshopfiles/?appid=2212330] Grapes [/url][/i]

LINK: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2984525577


-------

[b]BOG USES THE [I]NEW[/I] EXTRA COLOR SYSTEM, UPDATE YOUR STYLES AND SHOW OFF YOUR DRIP![/b]

[b] [url=https://discord.com/channels/1042370928195162132/1065719676241449062] BOG DISCUSSIONS ON DISCORD!![/url][/b]

[b][url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jClGguzCnIo]TRAILER BY DARK KRYSTAL[/url][/b]
[b][url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GfwU05DjZ4Q]2ND TRAILER BY NUION![/url][/b]


-------


[b]TIER: VANILLA[/b]
[b]Bog[/b] specializes in utilizing his [b][u]Blud Bugs[/u][/b], and is an all-around fighter, but is more [i]favored on the ground.[/i]
He can use his fast movement to evade and get in quickly, command grab the opponent for mega damage, counter and explode on them, or just [i]laugh in their face >:)[/i]
[i]Bog is fast and deals big damage, but loses health at the cost of using most attacks and requires [b]solid yomi[/b] in order to get in, punish, [u]deal monstrous damage, and feel like one while doing it[/u].[/i]


Bog also contains bit-crushed voice acting, just like Omen, by [b][i]Many Different Sources Including Myself[/i][/b]
[i]If you are familiar with my other mods, you may notice that Bog uses some of my Ninja skin animations, but better! all were animated in [b]Pivot[/b][/i]


-----------------

[h1][i]BLUD BUGS - CORE MECHANIC[/i][/h1]
[i]Some Attacks, Specials, and Supers will spawn [u]Blud Bugs[/u] that eat at Bog's health as they release, losing between 300 - 350 health, Supers spawn Blud Bugs too, but take significantly less health for more Blud Bugs. Their trajectory is random and Bog [u]cannot die to his own attacks.[/u][/i]
[i]Once a [u]Blud Bug[/u] drops on the ground, Bog gains access to [u]three new abilities[/u] using all of them at once.[/i]

[list]
[*][b]Spike[/b]: Blud Bug forms into a Spike, an OTG attack that launches the opponent
[*][b]Shoot[/b]: All Blud Bugs swarm at the opponent, dealing big damage and decent hitstun
[*][b]Heal[/b]: All Blud Bugs will home towards Bog and heal him for 200 Health
[/list]

[i]Use these tools to play passively and manage your health, or play oppressively and overwhelm your enemy at the perfect moment.[/i]

-----------------


Having trouble determining how much health you're losing and gaining? Download [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2932748036]Ranked Utilities by Degritone![/url]

If your experiencing health bar issues, please unsubscribe from the Custom Character UI Mod: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2944686292&searchtext=custom


-------


[b][i]TIPS:[/i][/b]
[list]
[*][i]Blud Bugs can be melee attacked and destroyed by projectiles[/i]
[*][i]"Super Dash" has projectile invulnerability[/i]
[*][i]"LVL1: EX Clutch" has projectile invulnerability on Initiative[/i]
[*][i]Blud Bugs cannot be parried, as well as "Blud: Slap"
[*][i]"Scream" is a counter, as well as a combo extender and anti-air, it begins as soon as Bog screams (Frame 7), the 5 Blud Bugs that spawn during a successful counter [u]do not[/u] take health[/i]
[*][i]"Bogatile" & "Lunge" have upper body invulnerability[/i]
[*]"Relentless" & "Clutch" have armor
[*][i]"Laugh" to gain a small amount of Super Meter[/i][/list]

author: AnAwesomeDudette
title: Boonewielder
description:
Boonewielder is a defensive powerhouse, updated for 1.9.0 and balanced around the Vanilla cast. 

They wield the Boone, an esoteric (fictional) ritualistic weapon, shaped from a shard of metal to be 40% sharp, and 60% blunt. It destroys many projectiles on contact, while controlling massive amounts of space.

Their main mechanic is passive meter generation, constantly gaining meter while not in hitstun. However, many of their options are dependent on meter or resources to use. Manage this properly, and aim with precision and destruction.

Yes, the character is a block. All moves are animated to the best of my ability, and the character may be updated with optional skin(s) to replace the block with a more humanoid design.

Special thanks to:

- ForsetCabiri - Absolute GOAT. Cracked. A big part of why I'm able to do this at all. Has contributed invaluable feedback and artworks.
- Wex - A great source of design feedback, concepts, and matches since the beginning. 
- TheBigSad - cracked :sob:
- DD - Support on my various projects for a very, very long time. Much love, much appreciation.
- VineRaio, roycebracket, 6A, Videofreak, hunter_, scrodumhat, & the unstable-hustle channel - Invaluable and varied feedback, gameplay, concepts, and laughs.
- Luantic - sneed
- My Wife - mah waif

Please report any bugs you find! The Boone's projectile-eating properties may not be rigorously tested against some modded characters. If some interactions don't play nice, or you encounter other bugs or crashes, please share! 

This character is Character Codex complete.

Inspired by Hakumen from BlazBlue.

title: Cestus - *punches you knightly*
description:
Cestus is a zoner-rushdown hybrid, capable of reaching you from far away since many of his attacks launch him like a cannon ball. (changed lol)

I'm not sure if Cestus is really in Beta still, but still let me know if you find any bugs or balancing issues (with preferably details and maybe suggestions) and ill try to fix em, thanks!
UPDATE: damn he old

Gimmicks to note:
- His main dash move (Launch) is only usable after a grounded dash or an attack.

- Has only one air option, but regains it after hitting the opponent with normal aerial attacks.

- Ballista can carry your opponent to the corner, although the range carried can vary by when and where it is used.

- Incinerate is a frame 3 move, but can only be used when interrupted during Launch, Dash Forward, Super Dash or Super Jump, and requires Cestus to be in contact with the opponent, due to its short range and Incinerate not being able to carry momentum well.
-- (If Incinerate is usable from any other move that isn't mentioned earlier, thats a bug)

- The amount of spears shot by Barrage will lessen the closer Cestus is to the wall.

- Pancake can be used to interrupt your opponent, but can heal them on hit. It can also bounce off your opponent and hit you, potentially putting yourself in a bad position, your enemy can also hit your pancake back at you. (And is also very punishable on parry/whiff)

- Shield Slide can be chained into itself, making Cestus do a faster and hyper-armored Shield Slide.
‎ ‎ - Hyper Shield Slide can also happen if Cestus' velocity is high enough on the ground (during a Super Dash or a Dash Forward at a specific time window)

Choso’s main game plan revolves around using his blood orbs to set up into a “Piercing Blood” hit. Using “Convergence” activates a blood orb that hovers around Choso (with a max of three). This gives the player access to several special attacks, “Meteorite”, and the option to send out a blood orb with “Discharge”. With a discharged orb on the map, the player can activate them with a couple actions like “Supernova” and “Monsoon” (with more to come), allowing Choso to pressure the enemy from far away.

[Scripter: Deroup]
[Spriter: Worminator]

Small Notes/Upcoming Plans:
This new overhaul for Choso is just the tip of the iceberg for us. Expect more Choso updates in the future, such as new stances and more supers. Maybe Choso might even call for the help of his brothers. Who knows what's to come.

author: BrebStyxo
title: Crossbones (dont cross him)
description:
Crossbones is a mostly a zoner, but still have somewhat good medium-ranged melee capabilities while also being able to threaten from far away. His general damage is also remarkable, being able to more or less consistently extend combos with his Seize and Wall Bone, and be able to do hard-hitting melee combos using his own gravestone cross as a weapon.

But here's the kicker: he (I THINK, i forgor) dies to a single palmstrike at full health. But! He has an extra lives mechanic, being able to respawn shortly after "dying", and also being able to gain extra lives at the cost of meter.

Oh and he has summons, and 4 types of them, with different movesets and health values. (Trust me, its actually balanced, relatively.)

Not sure if he's still in Beta, but he still has quite alot (if not a very concerning amount) of bugs and most likely balance issues. If you find any, let me know with details so I can (hopefully) fix it, thanks! (and yes ik about the prediction errors, kinda lazy to fix it but idk)

Cool mechanics to note:
- He has maximum 2 lives, and starts with max lives.
- His summons can be knocked down, rendering them unable to keep fighting, but can be revived via spending a life.
- When his normal health reaches 0, he will enter a dying state, he can still be comboed for extra meter and slight damage for his next life.
‎ - When in dying state and he hits/is on the ground, he will collapse, and his cross is sent flying away. Once the cross lands, he will respawn where the cross landed, play a lil respawning animation, will knock you away if you're too close, and then the game will continue like usual (supposedly).
- Many of his attacks do not do hitstun, and does Damage Over Time instead.
- Regaining a life will cost a varying amount of meter.
‎ - Using it for the 1st time will cost 1 bar
‎ - Using it for the 2nd time will cost 2 bars
‎ - Using it for the 3rd time will reach its max cost at 3 bars
‎ - Using it for the 4th, 5th, 6th, etc time will always cost 3 bars

P.S: hes not sans i swear
i also wonder if some people think he's using a greatsword

title: Damon - The Thunder Demon
description:
Inspired by the Mishimas (mostly Jin) from Tekken :)

Damon is a short range  fighter who excels when he is up close to his opponent.

Essential  moves:
Jab 3f - fastest attack he has that counters grab and forces a  mix up. However, it has a very short range where it will only hit if you are in close enough to the opponent.

Zen stance - A stance that gives you full of mix up options and also great for extending combo. (Best moves from the stance - Body blow 3f - short to mid, big damage. Side tap 6f - combo extender. )

Electric god fist 5f - costs 2 bars and deals massive damage. Has hyper armour and will go through hyper armoured moves. 

Lead knee 6f - Great for combos

Scissor kick 10f - high damage and evades low attacks. However, you splat on the ground depending how high up you are in the air, forcing you to get up.

Axe kick 12f - decent damage for a combo starter, launches opponent up and can hit downed opponent making them unable to manually get up or roll. It has slightly longer range than floor break.

Floor break 8f - can hit downed opponent but it is very short.

Demon pounce 12f - Costs 3 bars and can only be accessed after using floor break. Very high damage but it cannot be followed up after unless you are close to the wall the opponent is at.

Twin lift 10f - First kick can guard break. Best combo starter move but do not use it mid combo (unless they wall splat).

First ever mod so feel free to give feedback thx!

author: CrashV
title: Delinquent V2
description:
He's back and he's better.
The long awaited Delinquent revamp is here!

This is a all new character with a fully reanimated moveset.
although he is reanimated, there are plenty of moves pulled from the old delinquent, and some reimagined.

This version of him is a look of what old Delinquent could've been if i had more experience with not only spriting but coding as well.
I hope you all enjoy and as always, please let me know if I did a good job and/or any bugs you may come across.

Move set:

A lot of his moves are self explanatory but i'll outline his mechanics a bit.

Delinquent is a stance heavy character that is versatile against any opponent.

Base stance (Normal):
This is the shortest ranged stance good for up close combat.

Kick: This move houses 4 different kick moves that have different applications, Launching kick, Sweep, etc.

Yo-yo Sweep: Made for knocked down opponents (Works well with sweep or Windmill Trip)

Snatch-up (Aerial): Grabs opponents off the ground and puts them in position for you to extend combo.

Whip Stance (Semi-mid ranged):
longer ranged than Normal but still pretty short. Most moves in this stance are pretty obvious.

Shock Cannon: Probably the only move that isnt super obvious but its an anti-air/ combo finisher that hits diagonally upward.


Windmill Stance (Mid range):
This move is not only a stance but a soft projectile shield. the movement can be confusing, sometimes mistaken to be a move with a hit box but it only hits projectiles. On top of that all the normal attacks in this stance charges "Discharge" meter. (Discharge can also be gain every frame while holding)

Headache: The furthest hit box forces grounded, a good knock-up reset tool. Gains the least amount of discharge on use.

Pull: 2 hit move that pushes, then pulls the opponent toward you. Moderate discharge gain on use.

Trip: A sweep move with halved DI modifier. Helps reset momentum and helps set up for a finisher. Gains most discharge on use.


Dragon Stance (Long range):
Longest range stance by far. This stance can dominate at range but be careful mostly all the moves have a decent sized start up and cannot hit at close range. Most of these moves are used for reads and combo tools.


Lethal Mode:
A transformation that is kept even when attacked. this stance is a balance of short and long ranges by utilizing speed. Gains an air option.

Flash Kick: Quick steps directly in front, or behind the opponent and delivers a launching kick. This move also uses air options if used in the air. (Can hit aerial opponents and is full map ranged.)

Hallowed Ground: Strikes the ground sending electricity currents throughout. Some electricity lingers causing a magnetic field that slows opponents and builds "discharge".

Stab: A command grab that beats any regular grab. also a combo starter.



Discharge moves:
Moves that utilize the Discharge meter.

Unholy Light (Hallowed Ground): Must have at least 8% of discharge to perform. After using Hallowed Ground, Delinquent focuses the electricity into a narrow area creating a mark, at any point Delinquent can unleash the electricity that shoots out of the ground in that marked area piercing anything it comes in contact with. (Costs 8% of discharge)

Lightning Orb (Normal or Lethal): Must have at least 50% discharge. Summons an orb that hovers above the opponent striking them on command with a 50 tick cool down. (can be destroyed with attacks) (Each strike costs 10% of discharge)

Lightning Orb: Divine punishment: Every tick the lightning orb is above a "Hallowed Ground" magnetic zone the orb will grow in size until it reaches critical mass. The Orb becomes highly unstable and the slightest touch could make it explode. The strike becomes 3x stronger at triple the cost of discharge.

Thunder Crack (Windmill Stance): Must have full discharge. A super that costs no base game meter but will take all of your discharge.



If you have any questions regarding bugs, move set, etc, please text me in the discord server:
https://discord.com/channels/1042370928195162132/1277683643833122917

Credits:
Animations by Crash_V

Coding by crash_v, ._jynx and venrox45

Sfx by crash_v

Icons by crash_v and kanavaer

author: Hustler One
title: Doomsayer (LOB)
description:
A significant expansion and overhaul to Doomsayer, giving him a moveset on par with the vanilla cast while still retaining his gameplay style as an up-close and personal rushdown. His original moveset has been largely merged with Doomsayer R's moveset, and significantly altered to make him more viable and fun to play. Doomsayer has several new normals, specials, and supers, such as Crimson Dive, a new move that allows for him to hit the opponent OTG, and Thought Process, an aimable delayed projectile designed to give him a way to setup delayed pressure on the opponent. 

Some of Doomsayer's normals have altered properties on block, allowing for him to launch the opponent, pull/juggle them, and perform attacks with delayed cancels on block, allowing for him to create tricky situations for the opponent.

Doomsayer now has an additional projectile known as Blood Clot, which creates a puddle of blood that Doomsayer becomes frictionless upon stepping over, allowing him to move slightly faster and causing him to be able to reach immense speeds by building up momentum. This momentum can be retained in the air, so long as he does not touch the ground for too long. Hubris Crescent will also generate a trail of blood when used.

Additionally, Doomsayer gains an install, Forced Heart Attack, which grants him access to the ability to chain normals together into unparriable strings, along with several other smaller buffs to his neutral game. This comes at the cost of draining his health over time though, increasing in intensity over the duration of the install.

Doomsayer is also able to offensively utilize his Burst in neutral, allowing for punishing aggression from the opponent. Though, he will be at a significant disadvantage if the opponent blocks it.

Doomsayer has full style support as well, with his entire moveset being alterable by style colors



Credits:
Lx_Legacy: Literally did half the mod and a significant portion of the normals/special design, absolute damn legend.
Nova, Wex, SmallSlab: balancing feedback
THExplosion24: respriting basechar sprites
s.a.s.a.y._0w0: workshop icon
Nok: creating Doomsayer/TFA. 
Videofreak: Kicking off the whole idea for Doomsayer's initial conceptualization
Trimay: Fixed a large desync issue with Doomsayer's gimmick

	- Throwing a card (either Take a Chance or Winning Tickets) into a coin (either Penny Drop or Pocket Change) will superpower the card, causing it to become much faster, stronger and unblockable.
	- The moment a card makes contact with an opponent, you will become actionable.
	- The moment your character makes contact with one of your coins, you will consume the coin and become actionable. You will also gain a decent amount of meter.

author: Hustler One
title: Doubledown: Scholar of the First Sin
description:
Unofficial-semi official patch of Doubledown that implements radical changes to his gameplay to make him more competitively viable while nerfing some of his more unfair qualities.

STYLE SUPPORT NOW ADDED!

Extra Color 1 controls the color of cards (the red in particular), including blue particles. The color that normally corresponds to blue will be shifted towards a contrasting color of the color you picked.
Extra Color 2 controls the color of coins and yellow particles

Dash IASA at 10f
Readded multicard.
Taunt is now a regular Hustle.
0f movement added back to some moves in combo only (Risk is the big one).
DI modifier on normals increased to 1.0
DI modifier on specials increased but not as severely
Touching a coin in neutral will interrupt your opponent as well
Coins and card bounces will be affected by DI wheel similar to cowboy bullets or sunshower umbrellas
Infinite particle issue fixed
Coin cancel escape now instead scales the opponents combo and is delayed by 16 frames.
Risk doesn't take an air option in combo
The High Court Armor put to frame 3 minimum, only works on initiative for the armor. Opponent gets put into 10f hitstun if they attack DD with armor (mostly just a change to get it to actually work as a good reversal).
Blue Card doesnt get eaten on block or hit, meaning it can be bounced back into the opponent afterwards
DD now has a sweep move similar (read: exactly the same) as Mutant on the ground, name change pending
Stomp is frame 7, far sharper downward momentum
Roulette launches on block, IASA HIGHLY increased on block if not coin cancelled
Lowered friction (again)
Cards are +1, Blue cards are +2, regular cards are still parriable.
Cards now bounce on walls instead of gliding across them. This refreshes their hitbox
High Court can now be blown up with a coin.
High Court now acts like Flame Wave and is unparriable and multi hits 
Penny Drop is now unparriable and hits opponents twice on block, does not get consumed on block
Adjusted how coin cancels work internally for hopefully more consistency
High Card is Frame 5, High Card is now +1
Nerfed Blue Card damage (it was too evil)
Double Cross: First hitbox is now frame 5. First hitbox does less damage, second hitbox does more damage.
Nerfed Risk flip
Nerfed Reward flip
Nerfed Poker Trip flip
Nerfed Four of a Kind's movement
Nerfed Table Top flip
Blocking Risk now gives back air options (allows for chaining roulette in a blockstring)
Grab now is interruptible by coin cancel, provided that it would not cause a softlock (meaning, not during a throw)
Clockwise and Stomp no longer land cancel prematurely, heavily increased landing frames
Risk landing frames heavily increased

author: MiyuuKitzune
title: Engineer (v1.5)
description:
[h2] General Description [/h2]

Engineer is quick and aggressive hustler that can deal massive damage at closer ranges but can keep up the pressure at a distance as well. his main gimmick is that he has a draining battery that allows him to do his stronger moves, some moves can increase that battery by a little which encourages him to get rack up combos for more battery (Moves in description). While he is a strong choice, he may not be as good at medium range as he's not close enough to get in but also not far enough to be safe while setting up.


[h2] Battery Moves [/h2]

these are moves that increase or decrease battery (no particular order)

[/tr]

[td]-0[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Cable[/td]
[td]+10[/td]
[td]-0[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Electric shock[/td]
[td]+10[/td]
[td]-0[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Piston Gauntlet[/td]
[td]+5[/td]
[td]-8[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]

[td](-15 if powered)[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Rocket Launcher[/td]
[td]+0[/td]
[td]-20[/td]
[/tr]

[h2] Extra Mechanics [/h2]

[h3] The Drone [/h3]

The drone is similar to wizard orb however it carries some differences. for starters it's automated so engineer can sit back as it does most of the work, using its Charged button allows it to combo moves instead of it only doing one single attack (it'll do the attack opposite of the direction you initially picked). the moves also give a varying amount of battery (of which I will not be listing).

[h3] Overclock [/h3]

Overclock allows engineer to go into a sort of workaholic state, decreasing the time it takes for him to attack after hitting. it also does stops battery drain and resets pushback upon scoring a melee hit. you can extend the overclock state by hitting the opponent.

author: BrebStyxo
title: Galahad (shes galahad enough)
description:
Having fast but clunky/limited movement, Galahad is a hard-hitting tanky large fighter with a giant sword for big hitboxes with big damage. She's also kinda a grappler? Semi-grappler you could say. She also has a high-risk high-reward kinda playstyle, think of Robot, as she's more-or-less based on them.

For a funny sorta gimmick though, she has the usual guard breaks like Slash and Recovery, but her Halve and Smack can guard break as well when you knock them back to the wall. Halve is especially good at this as it excecutes way faster than the alternative Smack. (but Smack sends way farther, making wall guard breaks easier to do) 

I'm also planning for her to be a high-risk high-reward kinda character, think of Robot's COMMAND:GRAB (how it does so much damage but is very punishable) but like, with different variations.

Last thing to note is that she has her Will buff, which essentially just increases her attack speed (ex. her Smack's hitbox being f12 instead of f20), you can get it by using her Call of Will move, but you can also gain it by Super Dashing, Super Jumping, and Vault, but it only activates when you actually launch from the move. (ex. you wont be buffed if you Super Dash but haven't completed the dash part.) Using Call of Will gives you the longest duration of Will buff (300 ticks), second is Vault (125 ticks), third is Super Jump (100 ticks), last is Super Dash (50 ticks). And no, they don't stack.

author: Nuion
title: Gallade
description:
[h1] Gallade is 100% finished, try it out now!! [/h1]

Galllade is a Pokemon inspired character, using a Tag-Fighter Assist system.

Every attack/move is based on attacks from Pokemon and revolve around setplay, extensive and creative combos. This cahracter can also be played in different playstyles depending how you enjoy playing. Rushdown for example IS an option he has. Considering he does have "fireballs" and classic DPs, he would also be considered a shoto Fighter.

This is a huge Collaboration between Hibiki (did all the sprites) and I (Nuion, did coding and vfx).
This was only possible because j8bit_forager comissioned us on this.

Balancing was tested quite a bit. If you have any feedback or found bugs, or want to see more cool characters, join the community and see some Work In Progress content of talented creators or just contact me, join the Discord here: https://discord.gg/MjxbWrHQNA

[b]Moveset[/b]


[b]Normals[/b]

[b]Slash[/b] Universal main tool, use this to extend your combos
[b]Brick Break[/b] Pulls down, good for grounded combo extensions 
[b]Low Kick[/b] Hits low, pulls enemy towards you 
[b]Fury Cutter[/b] Multihit, can be cancelled every 3 hits
[b]X-Scissor[/b] Big damage but slow 
[b]Aqua Cutter[/b] Your shoto Dragon Punch uppercut, has super armor 
[b]Psycho Cut[/b] Main projectile tool, can hit close range, can be stringed into itself
[b]Leaf Blade[/b] 3 Hit Gap closer
[b]Shadow Claw[/b] Sends enemy downwards, good to ground enemy 


[b]Specials[/b]

[b]Aura Sphere[/b] Setplay projectile, can control speed. Also has knockback to get out of situations 
[b]Aerial Ace[/b] Aimable teleport with hitbox, good to follow up in difficult situation, does little damage, high damage poration 
[b]Stone Edge[/b] Creates Pillar on enemy from the ground. Good to create +Frames to setup. 
[b]Swift[/b] Shoots 3 diagonal projectiles with slightly randomized positioning 
[b]Swords Dance[/b] Damage buffs, lasts for the next 2 Hits (can be applied to anything, including supers), adds 20% damage.
[b]Ice Punch[/b] Freezes enemy in air, high knockback if you miss the unfreeze 



[b]Supers[/b]

[b]Gardevoir Assist[/b] Cost: 0 Bar. Spawns Gardevoir, she shoots out a black hole, pulls enemy in, has a hitbox. 
[b]Night Slash[/b] Cost: 1 Bar. Good damage, good framedata, big hitbox. Your bread and butter to add extra damage. 
[b]Iron Valiant Assist[/b] Cost: 2 Bar. Spawns Iron Valiant, they shoot spawn a huge slash on the enemy directly, does high damage, good for setplay and creates pressure 
[b]Mega Evolution - Giga Impact[/b] Cost: 3 bar, Transforms into Gallades Mega Evolution and does Giga Impact, does high damage and (should) always hit when you confirm with the initial hit. 


[b]Movement[/b]

[b]Teleport[/b] Teleports you a long distance, easy to punish since gallade already has many movement tools
[b]Double Team[/b] Gives Invincibility between frame 3 and 10

author: OpulentEnder
title: Gish
description:
Adds a new character, Gish.

The word "Gish" is a dungeons and dragons term that refers to a character that combines spellcasting with physical combat. And this character hopes to accomplish just that, providing a variety of verstaile and magical abilities.

This character has 6 attacks, 3 specials, and 3 supers.
Flourish: A basic versatile attack with short range and high damage.
Booming Blade: An attack with decent range and damage that has high horizontal knockback.
Arcane Pierce: An extemely fast attack with decent damage and a narrow range.
Flame Blade: A slow but powerful attack with a large hitbox.
Cyclone Slash: An attack that sends you upwards with a downwards hitbox that pulls in enemies hit by it.
Bolt Crush: An aerial move that sends you straight down, dealing good damage too.
Magic Knife: A small projectile with weak damage but high speed and homing.
Shadow Blade: A decent melee attack that creates a projectile.
Soaring Stab: An upwards attack that sends you flying upwards.
Misty Step: Use 1 level to teleport forward a distance of your choosing.
Blade of Disaster: Use 2 levels to make a slow but devestating attack with a gargantuan hitbox.
Steel Wind Strike: Use 3 levels to conjure 6 homing sword projectiles.

author: CutestGirlHere.
title: Goat.
description:
[h1] Charge headfirst into battle [/h1]

Goat is a close-range rushdown with limited air mobility and few ranged options. Thanks for her bulletproof horns, all horn-based attacks grant armor. Be careful overusing this, as she can develop a concussion after suffering too many blows to the head.

Please note that she is still currently a work in progress. Details can be found near the bottom.

[h1] Helpful tips [/h1]

[b] Trample and Pummel [/b] exclusively hit downed opponents. Use them after a knockdown to finish off a combo before the enemy can get up.

[b] Ground Pound and Crash Landing [/b] summons earth spikes that remain on the field. Spikes block enemy projectiles, or can be launched straight up with her Launch Spikes moves. They also serve as a hazard for anyone who lands on them.

[b] Take a Breather [/b] lets you reduce a large amount of your concussion meter. Concussion naturally lowers over time as long as its not maxed out. Avoid using armored moves at high concussion, or try to find a chance to rest mid-combat. Otherwise any armor hit at max concussion will leave you stunned.

[h1] Mod Progress [/h1]

8/8 Basic attacks, 8/6 Special attacks, 4/4 Supers, 6/6 Aerial Basics, and 5/4 Aerial Special are all complete for her moveset. More moves may be added beyond these initial goals.

There are some noticeable issues with sprites and animations that need touched up.

Damage and Hitstun are still in need of a lot of tweaking and balancing.

Some UI needs to be changed, such as her Throw Rocks move saying Jump Arc for a projectile.

Needs a lot of work done on particle effects, and adding a few more moves to fix holes in her kit.

[b] Please feel free to leave suggestions and feedback. [/b] Especially leave feedback on balancing, or move tweaks/additions that you think might be helpful to patch holes in her movelist.

author: Cel
title: Gorb
description:
Gorb is a silly little character I made for no reason other than to figure out how making mods in YOMI even works, because I’m very much new to this whole coding thing. He’s a gloopy shapeshifting setup zoner with powerful movement tools that as a zoner, allow him to make people miserable.

Gorb’s specials consist of 3 main parts that allow you to make people’s lives hell.

The Puddle (trademark patent pending) is a slow option that Gorb can only set up when far away or within a combo. Having a puddle out will let gorb teleport to it as a 5F option or transform it into a spike. The puddle is destructible however, because if it wasn’t it’d be kinda broken.

Upon using a teleport, you will leave a clone in your previous position. You can freely move the clone during your turn with UI, and can detonate it on command. If the opponent does strike the clone, the clone will detonate itself on its own, allowing itself to be a massive pain and powerful defensive tool.

Gorb can also summon corrosive gas, a powerful homing projectile that will deal damage for every tick you’re in it. Its slow speed and massive damage potential render it a strong area denial tool, though it does require 15 frames of startup to get off.

What a guy. Gorb. :)

author: TVFLabs
title: Hacker
description:
The Hacker is a new fighter that lets you write and run GDScript in-game.

It only has 2 moves: Write Code and Run Code.
Write Code lets you write code. You can continue writing the same script on your next move.
Run Code runs the code you have written, as the script of a Node2D called "Program" that's a child of the fighter.
For convenience, I've added 3 preset variables: `p1` and `p2` refer to Player 1 and Player 2 respectively, and `objects` is an array of all other objects (like projectiles).

UPDATE on December 10th 2023: If the game is online, Run Code does nothing. Well, I hope that's the case at least, but the fact is I don't have any way to test this. If it still works online, please let me know.
It's obviously not balanced in the slightest, and you're likely to crash the game while using it. Still though, it's pretty neat!
For now it uses mostly Ninja sprites, but that might change in the future.

author: DoYouSellVHS
title: HAG: Heavy Armor Garrison
description:
-==-      -==-
The Heavy Armor Garrison (henceforth referred to as the HAG) is an armored defense mech used to deter blithesome hustlers from fighting in YOMI city. For too long, powerful combatants have torn asunder the city streets, wrecking havoc as they fight with no holds barred. In response, a secret military corporation- YURAH (YOMI Underground Robotics Assembling Hustlers) Corp- had taken a contract with YOMI city to provide a mechanized defense solution.

The HAG is the first prototype of mech, deployed to prevent hustlers from enjoying their spars. While some hustlers actually enjoy fighting the HAG, YURAH corp promises that deadlier, far less entertaining machines are in the works.

Nonetheless, the city occasionally deploys these units to stop hustlers from fighting. They have mixed results, but that’s more than enough for the YOMI mayor (Ninja).
-==-      -==-

HAG is a one-of-a-kind MASSIVE combatant with multiple body parts that you can switch out mid-match! Maneuver a massive mech around as you try and strike foes in their most vulnerable moments- managing your massive blows and lurching speed against much more nimble foes!

author: OpulentEnder
title: Illithid
description:
This mod adds a new character to the game, Illithid. "Illithid" is a fancy term for Mind Flayers from dungeons and dragons. I decided to make one a playable character taking inspiration from both their depiction in D&D and in Baldur's Gate 3.

This character relies on their telekinesis special to grab opponents and follow up with more moves. Their attacks don't do a lot of damage on their own, but they combo very well, chipping away at opponents with fast combos. Their super move, extract brain is their biggest damage dealing move. Devastating an opponent if it is able to connect.

This charaacter features 7 attacks, 4 specials, a movement ability, and 2 supers.

Universal Attacks:
-Tentacle Whip: A basic short-ranged attack with mediocre damage but extra stun-time
-Force Tunnel: A fast attack that sends you forward but deals low damage.

Grounded Attacks:
-Mind Blast: A diagonal-up attack that deals decent damage.
-Grasping Tendrils: An attack that aims far in front of you and deals good damage.
-Psy-Crash: An attack that sends you forward and deals good damage but has high hit lag.

Aerial Attacks:
-Downward Mind Blast: Sends you towards your opponent with a diagonal-upl attack that deals decent damage.
-Psychic Stomp: Sends you straight down, deals high damage if you collide with your opponent but also unleashes a larger explosion that deals less damage.

Universal Specials:
-Mind Spike: Creates a small homing projectile that deals low damage.
-Telekinesis: Acts as a throw but with a larger reach but shorter stun.

Grounded Specials:
-Conjure Tendril: Creates a tentacle projectile that moves along the ground dealing decent damage.

Aerial Specials:
-Concentrated Blast: A projectile that spawns in a distance you choose, it deals decent damage but doesn't stun or have knockback.

Supers:
-Plane Shift: Costs 1 level of super, teleports you directly to your opponent.
-Extract Brain: A powerful melee attack that can hit multiple times, dealing high damage.

Movement:
-Levitate: Fly upwards a short distance in a direction you choose.

author: HitsuuDesu
title: Illuko : The Dynast of Brilliance [Echoes of Divinity : AstralWoven Bond]
description:
⚠︎ - THIS MOD CONTAINS FLASHING LIGHTS - ⚠︎
- If you don't like flashy, bright stuff, then don't download and leave me alone.
This is my way and style of using particles/effects and I won't change it for you.

After months and months of hard and exhausting work from me and my team, Illuko finally sees the light of day with her release!
As my first mod, I tried to pay justice to this original character I have for around 6 years or so, I gave my best to make her stand out from the rest.
From a bald character with a very mediocre moveset, I built a small community/group to help me with her progress, and thanks to them and their hard work and immense amounts of thoughts put in to her playstyle, and most notably her balancing, she is not a war crime anymore! [If you say otherwise, I will burn you, we worked hard on this okay]
Before 3 months or so, she will not receive any major changes, I am taking a break from perhaps modding in general.

✦ - Custom UI

author: PlantMan
title: ISAAC-(Joke Mod)
description: Isaac and his mother lived alone in a small house on a hill. Isaac kept to himself - drawing pictures and playing with his toys as his mom watched Christian broadcasts on the television. Life was simple and they were both happy. That was, until the day Isaac's mom heard a voice from above. "Your son has become corrupted by sin. He needs to be saved." "I will do my best to save him, my Lord," Isaac's mother replied, rushing into Isaac's room, removing all that was evil from his life. Again, the voice called to her. "Isaac's soul is still corrupt. He needs to be cut off from all that is evil in this world and confess his sins." "I will follow your instructions, Lord. I have faith in Thee," Isaac's mother replied, as she locked Isaac in his room away from the evils of the world. One last time, Isaac's mom heard the voice of God calling to her. "You've done as I've asked, but I still question your devotion to Me. To prove your faith, I will ask one more thing of you." "Yes, Lord. Anything," Isaac's mother begged. "To prove your love and devotion, I require a sacrifice. Your son, Isaac, will be this sacrifice. Go into his room and end his life, as an offering to Me to prove you love Me above all else." "Yes, Lord," she replied, grabbing a butcher's knife from the kitchen. Isaac, watching through a crack in his door, trembled in fear. Scrambling around his room to find a hiding place, he noticed a trapdoor to the basement, hidden under his rug. Without hesitation, he flung open the hatch, just as his mother burst through his door, and threw himself down into the unknown depths below.

author: AxNoodle
title: Jamiroquai
description:
Jamiroquai, the Unmoving Traveller

Apologies to Jay Kay.

The character is named after the band that made the famous song and music video, Virtual Insanity.
The moveset for the character is inspired from that music video, found here:
https://youtu.be/4JkIs37a2JE?si=mG5ntKBLUkekVzND
Almost all animations and option names are taken from the song.

I've also sourced a small number of animations and audio from their song Canned Heat:
https://youtu.be/vE4VlA_9OrI?si=vrFpnghcbgUzSxKy

And also some audio from these AI memes:
https://youtu.be/zd4oGwPXJqQ?si=nXTqaQK9A4x40JnH
https://twitter.com/shutdownhaha/status/1644327660456226827


----- Guide ------


-- Basic Attacks --

No Sound - Default grab
Pray - Jab. It's also a multihit.
A Wonder - A short-range overhead launcher.
Ties Of Earth - Ground only. Long-range and low hitbox that drags towards you.
New Technology - Aimable long-range hitbox that also drags.
No More - Aimable short-range hitbox that pushes away and down.
Nature's Way - Aerial only. A spike directly beneath you, and a weak hitbox elsewhere.

-- Additional Movement Options --

Canned Heat - Aerial option. Teleports you to the ground at a chosen distance in front or behind your current position, but is quite slow.

Magic Spell - The main way to get your mobility. You start everything on the stage moving (is Flippable). After you do, you can stop your furniture’s or everything’s movement at any time. Will also stop after any furniture reaches a wall or you are hit.
I’ll refer to this as “stage movement” from now on.



-- Specials --

Live Underground - Summons a bird projectile. Semi-homing.

Immerse in Sin - Quick slide backwards, summoning a roach projectile. It hits both players and is immune to stage movement.

So Insane - Quickly moves the stage; the only way in which you can do so in the air. You either keep the opponent or furniture in place during the movement. Not flippable.

Furniture - This summons the most important part of Jamiroquai, some furniture. While falling, it’s a spike. Afterward, its hitbox is active only whilst moving and its hitbox can be refreshed by some of the below moves. You can have up to 5 at once.

Things are Big - All furniture begins to grow. Whilst growing, it has a passive hitbox. Also refreshes the movement hitbox.

Should be Small - Grown furniture shrinks. Again, it has a passive hitbox and refreshes the movement hitbox.

Crazy World - All furniture explodes, dealing a lot of damage. Use with caution though - it’s a short-term investment of your furniture.



-- Supers --

Big Furniture - Level 1. Summons a larger sofa at a longer range.

Foolish Mind - Level 3. A long range guard break. Also refreshes furniture hitboxes.

Virtual Insanity - Level 9. Slides forward to initiate a cutscene. Instant kill.


There is now Mod Options support - you can use this to turn off most of the soundbytes.

I am very willing to take balancing advice, so please give me feedback of any kind!

author: Fathe321
title: Jinsoku, Mathematician SpellCrafter.
description:
Jinsoku, a really brittle character who takes two time the damage any other character would, he does not poses a block nor a grab, in return he is able to make use of his swift movement to dodge any incoming attacks at a specific frame on his current state. 
He uses a lil knife and his trusted MagiGun a wepon capable of spawning magic circles that, depending on the parameters YOU set will cast something different!

Jinsoku, has mentioned above has 2 weapons, a lil sword and a gun, he can work as a rush down and a zoner. 

Jin's gun has a spellsystem built into it, each spell circle its made put of the parameters "Type", "Target" and "Area"
these 3 parameters will decide what spells you are casting and upon changing one you change the whole spell. One circle
by itself can do a spell, this is called "SingleCasting"(Spells that are just a single circle), spells that consist of 2 circles on top of each other
are called DualCasting, and spells that are casted with 3 circles on top of each other are called "TripleCasting". There's two more way to cast spells
first its no spawning a single circle, this is called SelfCasting, and lastly, the act of casting a spell using not only circles BUT also SelfCasting, Mixed Casting.

There's the list of current existing combinations for spells, fell free to go to Jins Discussion post in Wip Mods Forum to suggest new combinations of spells!

- Single Casted:
    - Press = Type: Weight, Target: opponent or Objects, Area: AOA
    - Agravio = Type: Weight, Target: Opponent, Area: Single Target
    - PhononMaser = Type: Oscillation, Target: Opponent, Area: SingleTarget
    - Launcher = Type: Movement, Target: Opponent or Objects, Area: SingleTarget
    - GravitationPull  = Type: Acceleration, Target: Opponent, Area: AOA
    - ActiveAirMine = Type: Oscillation, Target: Space, Area: AOA
    - ProjectilePull =  Type: Acceleration, Target: Objects, Area: AOA
    - AirBullet =  Type: Converge, Target: Opponent, Area: SingleTarget


- Dual Casted:
    - WindBlade = Type: Convergence/Movement, Target: Opponent, Area: SingleTarget
    - DancingBlaze = Type: Acceleration/Movement, Target: Objects, Area: SingleTarget
    - ThunderChild = Type: Disperse/Converge, Target: Opponent, Area: SingleTarget
	- PerfectMissiles= Type: Oscilation/Movement, Target: Opponent, Area: SingleTarget

- Triple Casted:
    - HaleParticles = Type: Convergence/Release/Acceleration, Target: Opponent, Area: SingleTarget


- Mixed Casted:
    - MockTeleportation 1 = Type: Disperse, Target: Self  
    - MockTeleportation2 = Type Weight/Convergence/Movement, Target: Space, Area: AOA
    - SpatialBurst 1 = Type: Oscilation/Movement, Target: Self, Area: No specific
    - SpatialBurst2 = Type: Release/Converge/Disperse, Target: Space, Area: AOA
	
	- Made for DOJOs Saiverse Event!

Pierce - launcher

author: MowMeow
title: KAZUYA MISHIMA
description:
A TEKKEN guy. Includes almost all of his TEKKEN 7 move set. I may not bother balancing this.

Each color on the move icons represents a property the move has. Maybe don't bother memorizing these, use them to find similar moves.

He has too many moves, so I had to rework the move selection sections. From the outside of the screen to the "Lock In" button, the sections are: Left Punch, Right Punch, Left Kick, Right Punch, Movement/Defense.

He has 4 levels of supers. Level 1 supers are Devil moves, Level 2 supers are TEKKEN 7 supers, Level 3 supers are from crossovers, and the level 4 super is from TEKKEN 8.

Sidestepping moves have invincibility, moves that spin the opponent are represented by re-stand moves, and crouching attacks make Kazuya shorter.

Kazuya has many "stances," the most important of which being Crouch Dash. It shrinks your hurt box and you can back dash out of it, but you can not block. Most of his stances exist solely to allow him to choose a follow up. Since these are the only moves that you can cancel on hit, these are the only moves you can offensive burst out of.

Pride update:
Colors upon ye. Check the change notes if you want to see what they mean.

author: EndlessEcho
title: Korra - The Avatar (WIP)
description:
Korra joins YOMI Hustle as mid to close range fighter using her mastery of the four elements.
This mod is still in its very early stages and serves mostly as a proof of concept.
I decided to upload it as it currently is so that I can collect feedback I can use going forward.
The next update will probably be the inclusion of more basic animations, I may have got too focused on attacks first.
Animations and effects may not be final, I'll likely go back to touch up things here and there.
I hope you're excited to try Korra out! Let me know what you think, it keeps me motivated!

Her are some of the plans going forward.

MOVESET
Korra is an aggressive fighter who’s all about putting pressure on the enemy. She uses her versatile moveset to keep them at bay until she creates an opening to move in. So far, I’ve been thinking about her future moveset like this:
Characters generally have, or have space for, 18 standard moves: 9 normals and 9 specials. For her grounded moveset, I plan for Korra’s moveset to be divided as such: 4 standard melee moves, 4 fire moves, 4 earth moves, 3 water moves, and 2 air moves, and grab. Air takes a backseat during grounded combat because Korra will be unable to use earth in her aerial moveset, which I plan to be: 4 air moves, 3 fire moves, 2 melee moves, 2 water moves, and grab.
Even when she’s down, she’s not out. When Korra gets knocked down, I plan to include two moves that’ll be able to throw opponents off balance.

SPECIAL MECHANICS
Korra is going to have two signature moves
-A combo move that you acquire from landing four different elemental attacks in a row
-The avatar state
I don’t have much planned in detail for the avatar state, just concepts. She will get new moves that do high damage, but have low hit stun. This is because in the avatar state, I want it to feel more like you’re trading blows with a powerful opponent rather than just getting comboed again. She will have access to flight movement.

Unfortunately, WaterJets is benched for the time being until I can figure out why it makes the game crash.

author: Nuion
title: Machina
description:
2B from Nier Automata is joining Yomi Hustle!

[b] THIS CHARACTER IS NOT FULLY BALANCED YET. MULTIPLE BALANCE CHANGES ARE COMING SOON BASED ON FEEDBACK FROM THE COMMUNITY[/b]

This was a collaboration with the great Violetite and Nuion. This was made possible as a comission by Neon Nya.
Violetite did all the sprites and icons.
Nuion did the coding, balancing and engine stuff.


Machina is an all rounder with a unique move set allowing for creative combo routes and frame traps. Most of her moves are heavily disjointed and require precision to pull off. She is accompanied by 3 different "followers" her 2 swords "Virtuous Treaty" and "Beastlord" as well as her "Pod". The swords are purely visual but recreate the functionality within Nier Automata. The Pods placement only matters during ranged attacks.

- She uses her light sword the "Virtuous Treaty" for fast and agile attacks. 
- For her heavy weapon she wields the "Beastlord" sword, with slow but high damaging moves. 
- Utility wise she has her trusty "Pod", a small flying robot that accompanies her firing ranged attacks.

Machina is a new take on aerial combat, her attacks lock her into place to do devastating aerial combos. This is very similar to how 2B works in Nier Automata.

[b]MOVESET[/b]

[b]Normals[/b]

Twin Slash (f5, f10) - Your bread and butter good overall damage and speed to win neutrals and extend combos.

Horizon Slicer (f10, f16) - Heavy Sword spin with 2 strong hits while moving backwards.

Twirl (f7, f11, f15, f19, f23, f27) - A light gap closing multi hit move, she first moves backwards and then forwards at high speeds, allowing for defensive and offensive options within the same attack.

Blade Dance (f14,f20,f25) - Three hits, Heavy, Light, Heavy. This move does huge amounts of damage.

Rising Spiral (f9,f14,f19) - Heavy rising attack, dragging the enemies up, this move has complex hitboxes with sweet and sour spots rewarding precision.

Kick (f8) - A simple short range kick to launch the opponent upwards.

[b]Specials[/b]

Distant Slam (f11) - A long range heavy slam to extend combos and initiate ground bounces onto the opponent, has guard break.

Cleave (f10,f12...) - Aerial - Heavy aerial spin into slamming down with the sword until you reach the ground. This is a unique move that can be used in various ways but allows to drag the opponent back towards the ground and follow up with another attack.

Spinning Toss (f10, f11...) - Machina tosses her light sword forward creating a short time multi hit hazard.

Laser (f50) - Command your robot to attack with a short range multi hit laser. It tracks at the beginning of the move.

Heel Guillotine - (f5) - Aerial - A hit grab using her heel. Once grabbed she will fly with the opponent all the way to the ground with a big slam impact.

[b]Supers[/b]

Charged Laser - 2 bars - (f50) - Command the Pod to attack using a long range Laser.

Mirage - 3 bars - (f14, f16, f18, f20, f22, f24) - Machina disappears to unleash a strong multi hit flurry around her.

SELF DESTRUCT - 5 bars - (f20) - A huge self destructing blast. This move will always leaves Machina with 1HP and a regenerate aura that heals her 500 hit points over time. This is a very risky move.

[b]Utility[/b]
Perfect Dode - (f4-f10) - Super Armor counter that freezes enemy when hit. She still takes damage.
