author: Worminator
title: Messiah [Happy Chaos]
description:
[h3][u]Even someone as powerful as the original pioneer of Magic gets bored sometimes. [/u][/h3]

Messiah has 2 resources to manage, Concentration (300 MAX), and Bullets (6 MAX).

Messiah is able to fire his gun by entering either of his shooting stances, At The Ready or Steady Aim. While in either shooting stance, Messiah has a reduced moveset, greatly limiting his movement especially in Steady Aim.

This gun is a complete free action besides from entering the stance.

On entering these stances, a reticle will spawn on/near the opponent. 

[h3]Reticle[/h3]
Before Messiah is able to fire his gun in At The Ready or Steady Aim, his reticle must overlap the opponent for 15 ticks.

The shape of the reticle determines what state it is in. 

[b]Dot/Point[/b] : Reticle is not on the opponent
[b]Plus[/b] : Reticle overlaps the opponent
[b]X[/b] : Reticle is ready to fire

The countdown to fire appears next to the concentration bar.

Shooting drains 40 concentration (less in certain situations).

[h3]At The Ready[/h3]
At The Ready is Messiah's first shooting stance. 
    
[b]In this stance:[/b][list]
    [*]Movement is limited to Walk Forward/Backward
    [*]Moveset is restricted
    [*]The player gains the ability to manually aim the reticle, as well as an auto aim (auto aim drains extra concentration)
    [*]The reticle spawns away from the opponent
    [*]Concentration is slowly drained
    [*]Manual shots only drain 15 Concentration
[/list]

[h3]Steady Aim[/h3]
Steady Aim is Messiah's second shooting stance. 
    
[b]In this stance:[/b][list]
    [*]There is zero access to movement
    [*]Moveset is greatly restricted
    [*]Reticle has much faster tracking
    [*]The reticle spawns on top of the opponent
    [*]Aimable reticle offset when entering the stance
    [*]No access to manual aim
    [*]Concentration is decently drained
[/list]

[i]Read Messiah's [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3165815605&searchtext=codex]Codex[/url] for more info[/i]

[b]Created by:[/b][list]
    [*]Worminator (Spriter)
    [*]deroup (Coder)
[/list]

[b]Special thanks to:[/b][list]
    [*]Chiupel (For creating the Deus Ex Machina Cutscene)
    [*]Trangoe (Help with overall balance/ideas)
[/list]

author: Jareix
title: Metatherm [Thermodynamics Weaponized]
description:
You are a practicioner of metathermics, a dynamic setup playstyle featuring unique interactions between their own projectiles, with capabilities augmented by their running "temperature".
Just so happens you are also a ratfolk. Aka, 32 pixels of condensed bastard.

tl;dr: hit the purple with hot/cold, learn from there

advanced explanation
Your primary strategy: chuck stuff out, prepare a setup, and watch what happens when you burn, freeze, or "conduct" it in the face of an enemy. 
Your secondary strategy: manage your temperature to not explode, increase damage of your attacks, and use cold to build up "ice armor"
Your tertiary strategy: explode violently because you punched an open flame with a fistfull of "thermoconductive fluid."
Your quaterinary strategy: explode violently because you decided it'd be a great way to use a "cold" attack to draw in more heat when already "hyperthermic"
Your quinterinary strategy: explode, but cutely.

The path of the metatherm is by no means an easy one, and will require practice and experimentation to master.
But in doing so, you will become a literal force of nature, bending the laws of physics to lay waste to your foes.
Stay icy-hot, be patient, and learn to revel in self-destructive chaos as you unleash the fury thermodynamic discord.

Basic ideas:
Project purple 'conductive' mist/bolt attacks and use heat to detonate them in an explosion or cold to freeze them to deadly icicles.
Enhance your defenses with "Ice armor," allowing you precious turns to set up for attacks
Manipulate the temperature of the air to create powerful wind funnels and drafts to both navigate the stage and manipulate the trajectory of projectiles. You can even use "Super airblast" to send a sparkbomb right at its caster.
Take advantage of the interactions between your projectiles and temperature to create unique, with differentials creating unique effects ranging from small explosions to opponent-drawing vortices.

Create  "Stasis Drafts" to freeze your own projectiles in place, creating a space to prepare your barrage of icicles or a deadly trap explosive gas waiting for you to set off. (or just let your foe run into some fireballs..)

author: FatYoshi69
title: Mothman
description:
Character for the M4 jam, under the theme Fearful Folklore.
Design and coding by FatYoshi, spriting by Sean.

Special thanks to Somb (mrmcmantis) and Real for playtesting and feedback.


Moveset breakdown:

Mothman's main mechanic is the Rot status, the numbers that appear above him and his opponent. For every stack of Rot, the character's frame advantage on both hit and block is reduced, maxing out at 3 stacks. Additionally, the majority of Mothman's moves interact with his or his opponent's Rot in various ways.
Mothman can build Rot on himself by using Decay or Wings of Desolation, and transfer it to the opponent on hit or block using his normals with green corners. The opponent can also reduce their Rot by parrying or connecting attacks on hit or block.

The way each of the specials and supers interact with rot is as follows:
- Kiss of Death: On hit, maxes out the opponent's rot.
- Paralyze: On hit, consumes all of the opponent's rot for a stun that lasts a number of turns equal to the amount of rot they had.
- Shriek: If the opponent has at least one stack of Rot, gains a hit of armor.
- Darkness Dive: On hit, consumes all of the opponent's Rot, and drags them a longer distance and does more damage the more Rot they had.
- Multiplication/Ravage: shot moths apply one stack of Rot on block. Hitting a free moth will instead cause it to pop, applying Rot to any nearby player.
- Regeneration: heals 1 Rot at the cost of 1 bar.
- Stalk: Recovers more quickly the more Rot the opponent has.
- Intoxicate: consumes all of Mothman's Rot to spawn a cloud, which sticks to the opponent on contact and debuffs them, causing any attack they block or get hit by to increase their Rot. The cloud stays out longer the more Rot was spent to create it.
- Rebirth: On hit, Mothman melts, clearing all his Rot and doing a massive attack, whose damage is proportional to the amount of Rot he had. Additionally, it gains invulnerability on startup if used with at least 2 Rot.

Mothman also gains a passive 5% damage boost for each stack of Rot on the opponent.

(Ps, note by Sean, theres an alternate animation for one of the moves, go ahead and find it :)

title: Natasha
description:
The little sister of 3 brothers.

Natasha's unique in a way that her gameplay style comes straight from Mother Russia Bleeds
a beat em up game set in Russia on the verge of revolution.  
Her unique gameplay comes in form her
low damage but easily gained super meter, that meter is then used on her unique move called "topple"
located in her "special" section of her moveset.  When an opponent is knocked down, she can use "topple" to mount the opponent and either pummel them for damage using the super meter she has gathered through the combo
OR use the meter to Draw Nekro, a unique meter to Natasha

Nekro is used for powerful buffs that will give her sure advantage for her next neutral
so far Ive implemented these Nekro effects
1. Kremlin Colonel: 40%
- gain a draining 225 overheal (can stack)

2. Orange Tundra: 50%
- gain 2 charges of a toggle teleport behind your enemy
(6 frames of lag and teleports on frame 3)

3. Bloody Marry: 55%
- gain 1 charge of a unique grab attack option (she has the old yomi grab), a high damage attack that RESETS your combo, letting you deal high damage again

4. God-Mother: 100%
xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx



ps. I still have things to add, like her hussle or an intro. but honestly after such a long time of development, I wanna put out here and get some feedback while I can, thank you.

author: Izabba0027
title: Orbs Of Power
description:
My Second Mod!

This Character has multiple different attacks, all with a variety of uses in combat.
This Character also takes 2.5 times more damage than a regular character, so play carefully.

Basic Attacks.
Ember: Multi hit attack(s) that have medium range and medium damage. can aim in any direction.

Ice Spike(s) Multi hit attack(s) that have Low range and Medium damage. The Ice spike up launches you up while Ice spike down launches you down; Regular ice spike can aim in any direction.

Thunder Strike(s): Multi hit attack(s) that have Low range and High damage. The Thunder Strike up launches you Down while Thunder Strike down launches you Up; The regular thunder strike pulls enemies towards you.

Movement Attacks.
Rush: Throws you forward at high speeds dealing medium damage at a high range.

Blizzard: Lifts you forward and up at high speeds dealing medium damage at a high range.

Special Attacks.
Inferno: A Multi Hit attack that deals medium damage at a low range, it also launches you upwards.

Ice Slam: A Strong Hitting attack that deals high damage at a low range, this also activates Ice Rod Combo's

Lightning Crack: A Multi hitting attack that deals high damage at a low range, this also activates Thunder Whip Combo's

Fire Fist: A Multi hitting attack that deals medium damage at a medium range, hits diagonally and activates Fire Fist Combo's

Lightning Pierce(s): Diagonal attacks that hit both low and high for medium damage with medium range.

Melting Cut: A Strong hitting multi attack that deals High damage with low range; can be used to cancel the Ice Rod Combo.

Ice Rod Combo's.
Ice Spinner: A Multi hitting attack that deals low damage at a medium range, a very fast attack though.

Tri - Strike: A Multi hitting attack that deals medium damage at a low range, a very fast attack though.

author: BrebStyxo
title: Pancake Lady (comically sturdy pan)
description:
Pancake Lady is a pure rushdown, being able to get right into your face with movement options as fast (if not faster) than Ninja themselves.

P.Lady is kinda not in beta anymore, but hey if you have any opinions n stuff on what to nerf/change/etc, let me know!
(also i should probably give her more specials but eh lazy)

Funky mechanics to preferably know about:

- She can throw out coins and hit said coins to activate its hitbox and make it home to the opponent, initial direction affected by your DI wheel.
- Coins can be hit by your opponent (not right after throwing it, since it kinda just made it a counter move) and is still affected by your DI wheel, meaning you can make them hit your own coin and it would reflect back at them (yes, +CHARGEBACK, kind of.)
- Her slide is capable of many things: carrying speed, reversing speed and increasing speed via slide stacking (spamming slide over and over).
- Her air dashes have high air resistance (technically), and sometimes you can bounce off the floor when airdashing towards it.
- Her special Feed Back move has a timing mechanic, requiring you to set the timing correctly for the parry to connect, dealing considerable damage.
- Doing a Forward Dash Jump while having enough speed will make it do a faster (but higher iasa) dash jump.
- Throwing out a coin is affected by your current velocity. (if youre going left, the coin will kinda go left too)

P.S: we do a little ultrakilling

author: magneter06
title: Percht
description:
VERSION 0.2 IS OUT! Check the Change Notes above.

A mod for the Modded Mountain Modding Marmelade jam, under the theme "Fearful Folklore"

A Percht is a being originating from Pre-Christian Alpine Folklore, which emerge in December, ringing Bells and cracking Whips as to drive away the Winter Spirits and bring upon a fruitfull Spring Season.

Gameplay description:

Percht is a character who can switch between two forms, Schönpercht ("Pretty") and Schiachpercht ("Ugly"), which give him access to an entirely different moveset each.
He can change between the forms either by using the Change Form special or by using moves with the "Quickswap" toggle (which acts similarily to Cowboy's Draw and Robot's Drive)

In the Pretty form, Percht can use Smoke Cloud and the Smokescreen Super to summon smoke.
While Percht is standing in smoke created by him, he can use the Smokeshift toggle - this will destroy the smoke projectile Percht was standing in and will start moving him towards the position of another chosen smoke projectile. Using Smokeshift targetting a smoke projectile which is above ground will apply a short burst of force towards it. Using Smokeshift applies a 2 frames penalty/delay to Percht's current move.
In the Ugly form, Percht can blow up smoke projectiles with any of his fire moves. The explosion will also explode nearby smoke, causing a chain reaction.

In the Pretty form, Percht has a few whip-based moves. Using a whip based move (or Hustle) will decrease the start up of the next consecutive whip-based move by 3 frames.

author: Jareix
title: Protowolf
description:
You are an imperfect prototype of "Project Razorwolf", a cybernetically enhanced "clone" of a ruthless hunter-killer, lobotomized into obedience. 
Armed with brutal shredding jaws, light refractive fur, a holographic decoy, and a short range targeted teleporter, dominate your foes with merciless brutality and savage cunning.
Most crucial will be use of your decoy, swapping places with it both to create opportunities to exploit, and to prevent your prey from escaping as your claws and jaws rend them apart .
Go forth, hunt your quarry, make them bleed, make them fear you.
----
Protowolf  is a trickster-setup character based primarily around dominating neutral through careful management of her Decoy, Cloak, Killer Stance, and Bleed Stacks.
Key to your success as her will be utilizing your "Decoy" to its fullest potential. Think of it almost as a foresight with legs that doesnt go away. Quick, projectile immune, and able to be swapped with as a free action, this will be your most crucial tool.
Meanwhile, entering "Killer" stance through any "killer" movement option (stride, leap, pursuit, etc.), enhance her attacks and allow them to deal damage through  "hermorhage" stacks, rather than outright combo damage.
These "bleed" stacks deal 1 damage every 15 ticks, growing progressively slower as their health declines, but proc more quickly the closer you are.
More than that however, bleed stacks can enhance her various abilities, especially 'killer' moves. Ones of note is the upgraded blockstun of her "Carnivore" attack, and the enhanced mobility of her "bloodhound" movement option.
Her damage might seem sub-par, but her survivability and ruthless neutral potential more than makes up for it.
Nothing in prediciton will be false, so the canny opponent will be able to read you, so your opponent will be able to find you if you don't play slippery.
Regardless, play to her advantages, play to your opponent's mind, and you will find her to be a terrifying force to be reckoned with.

author: NuggetB
title: Puppet (WIP)
description:
Puppet is an unfinished character based
on the game of Undertale.
They boast a large amount of moves, slow
speed, and a great amount of pressure and
defense. However...these do not come free.
The gauge Puppet has is called the Morality
Gauge, it dictates how close you are to being
placed on a route. 

Merciful: The control route. This route uses unconventional attacks
to cover and punish even niche situations, as well as having access to an entire summon.
These summons (although there's only 1 right now) can either act as additional characters
or just a hazard for the opponent. Puppet still has to tell them what to do though.

Maniacal: The offense oriented route, loses
access to their best defense in exchange
for more freedom of use of Weapons, the
ability to do their Superdash, and better
speed.

Neutral: The default, has bad speed in
exhange for having the most freedom of
both routes. This route also benefits the most out
of the Armors out of all other routes.

And if you're wondering, yes I uploaded this twice, thanks steam.

author: AxNoodle
title: RKBee
description:
RKBee, Knifebearer of the Revel

A half-joke summoner-type character made for D.O.J.O.'s RKC event.

The character's animation was based on the video by TerminalMontage found here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xezfkm4w5Oo

The music used is the title screen theme for Buck Bumble, found here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K0DDY299Ly4

(NOTE: There is Mod Options support for this character - you can turn off the music from there.)

===== Guide =====
The character is quite simple, in principle, as there aren't many moves to pick from. 
Using the character well therefore depends on your manipulation of those moves.

== The Gimmick ==
RKBee has no attacks. Well... sort of. 
The bee itself has a grab but all other moves instead command your knives.
Knives will, at most times, attempt to travel towards you. You can offset where they're attempting to move by using the Push UI available to you at all times.
You start with one knife, and can get more as the game progresses, up to 4.
RKBee is very vulnerable if the knives aren't nearby - managing their location is important playing both with and against them.

== Basic Attacks ==

Slash - Command all knives to make a quick, light attack. They also get a burst of horizontal speed influenced by your Push.
Bash - Command all knives to stop where they are and dash toward the enemy. During this attack, you cannot influence the knives much. They do get a burst of Push-able vertical movement to begin with, though.
Thrash - Command all knives to spin for a multihit attack. They also get a burst of vertical speed influenced by your Push.
Quash - Basic Grab/Throw.

== Special Moves ==

Flash - Switch places with your original knife. You will be vulnerable for a while after teleporting. Only available if you have at least 1 bar of super, but costs none.
Leash - Accelerate knives' movement back towards you, influenced by Push. RKBee is very vulnerable if the knives aren't close, so make good use of this. It can also be used to influence their movement mid-attack.
Lash - Accelerate knives' movement entirely dependent on Push. Only unused knives will accelerate.

== Super Moves ==

Awash - Summon a new knife, but become vulnerable for a while. Requires 3 bars of super and consumes 2.
Gash - Command all knives to teleport (influcenced by Push), then deliver a large sweeping strike, spiking the enemy into the ground and dealing heavy damage. Requires 4 bars of super and consumes 3.



===== RKC Lore =====

The RKBee is a mutated and sentient bumblebee, created after an insect colony were exposed to experimental magitech chemicals. 
After gaining consciousness, the affected bees found their calling in dance, revelling in their newfound understanding in the world. This group would come to be known as the Revelbees. 
All was well in the insect world, until a red harbinger of chaos arrived in the form of a Blade of Old. A red knife.
Fighting broke out over the artifact, leaving the insect community all but exterminated. But one of these insects would not give up on dancing to their own tune.
Putting all of their newfound heart into dancing, the RKBee managed to speak to a will deep within the knife that caused it to dance along.
The insect war soon ended as the knife took on a life of its own, unwilling to be subject to use in such futile violence. It now uses its power to defend the Revelbees, following the best of them all - the one now known as the Red Knife Bee.

This knife was derived from an Old One more peaceful than most. Whilst the war raged outside, they found solace in dancing, uninvolved with the ideals of the others, uncaring of the bloodshed others brought upon themselves. They possessed the power of the True Illusion, capable of creating illusory clones of themselves with a physical presence. This One needed not its pugnacious brethren, for it was its own best partner in dance.

description:
"When the Angel appears... The underground will be empty."

Harness your inner king, conqueror, and emperor. Unleash your might upon those whose path lead them to you. Save your kingdom. Save your people.
Show them what happens when you stand against ROYALTY.

-----

Hey! I'm Pix, creator of the mod. The initial release of the mod is currently in a mildly unfinished state, though I wanted to try to see if I could get this done for New Years. There are still several things I wish I could have added, but that'll be for future updates. I have even bigger projects ahead of me that I wish to complete.
Though while I'm here, I figure I'd give a few notes since people seem to enjoy a small-
CHARACTER BREAKDOWN:

The character is a DUO character. They both share the same HP.
KING is a lot slower, though the melee range he has with his trident makes it easy to get in and keep the opponent in. They are bulky and hard to get off the ground, both for you and your opponent.
QUEEN is more nimble, and air heavy. She has access to more air options, and her fire based projectiles make her a force that keeps the opponent on guard and in check.
COMBINED they share 3 normals, and when they both undergo their transformation... The prophecy of the DELTARUNE will appear. The Angel will return. And it shall pass judgement on any who cross their paths.

(They also have 350+ unique character interactions. Look forward to that, lol)

... I pray that's a good enough breakdown! Otherwise enjoy the character!

(Do note that there are a few things that may be greyed out or only appear in infinite resources. Keep in mind those are not functional as intended yet and will be added in later updates! So stay tuned.)

author: LuiXee
title: Ryomen Sukuna, The King Of Curses
description:
IT WILL BE A MASSACRE!
A character who closes up gaps easily as well as baiting people with moves, he is better in grounded combos, use that for your advantage! cut people into pieces while getting stronger and land some black flashes.
Remember is a WIP so there's stuff for the future.

[h1] Common Questions [/h1]

-What is Extra action UI?
that's how i'll call the UI that some attacks have, this UI allows the player to select one ability to execute with the 2 arms at the same time you use the other 2, this only comes with some attacks.
most of the attacks have different types of the same attack, as example, "punch" from punch, is different than "punch" from back hand hit.
how do the Extra action attacks differ one from each other?
punch usually has from 30 to 45 dmg (6-8 f)
double punch has from 20 to 30 dmg per hit, more hitlag than hook punch(12-20 f)
hook punch has 50 to 60 dmg, low knockback (10-16 f)
dismantle has 20 to 30 dmg, having 20 f of hitlag and a large hitbox (most of it takes 30 f, excepting catch up dismantle, taking 12 f)
uppercut ...
grab deals 15 dmg and has 25f of hitlag (less range than dismantle, ( .... ))
YOU CAN'T INTERRUPT AN EXTRA ACTION ATTACK, you have to wait until it's over to use another extra action.
if the opponent hits you, the extra action will be interrupted.
most of the attacks will have a higher iasa if you select an extra action, so there's also a "Wait" action (0 f) that doesn't affect the iasa.
also, hitting the opponent with these attacks highers the chance for a black flash by 1%


this notes could be outdated-----



-Domain??? yes, to use it you need to use 4 black flashes

-Curse energy punch has a 10% chance of turning into black flash, the chance increases by hitting the opponent. black flash will upgrade the basic attacks, the 2nd black flash will increase the specials, and the 4th one will allow you to use the domain

-THE MULTIHIT MOVES ARE ACTUALLY PARRIABLE, but for some reason the game doesn't do it automatically

-Psycho laugh makes the chances increase +2 instead of +1 per hit, this effect stays until you land a black flash

-For people who don't know what chants do, when u use it 3 times, you get new and stronger supers (those supers also cost bars) once you use one of those, chants resets

-to use fire arrow you need to land 3 black flashes, use cleave and use dismantle (dismantle swing does not count), costs 7 bars: unblockable and fast projectile with massive dmg, not aimable, goes in a straight line.

author: JER
title: Sans - Skeletal Judgement
description:
Sans the skeleton hustle his ways with skele-tons of blasters

A zoner type character that specialize in bones and blasters
This character have a pretty complex gimmick

Here's the explanation
[[Passive]]
Stamina: Instead of HP, Sans uses Stamina to survive

Stamina Regen: When in "Wait" state, Sans will regenerate 0.7% Stamina every tick

Stress Meter: A bar that is indicated as Sans' eye will fill up and upgrade attacks when a certain treshold is reached

Dodge: Sans will teleport in a set direction on getting hit and loses a fixed amount of stamina and gain 3% Stress

"Weakest" Monster: Almost every move will only deal 1 Damage/Tick

Karma: Every damage dealt to the enemy will inflict KR. The higher the KR, the faster they will take damage from it

Phase: When HP is low or when Stress Meter is full, sans will enter his next phase

Phase 2: Every time sans is hit 3 bones will fall from the sky

Phase 3(Finale): Sans' will enter Retribution mode where he regain 1/3 of his stamina and won't consume Stamina or adds up Stress when using a move

Tired: Can't move, 1 hit and you are out

Movement: Consume 1% Stamina (except "Walk Forward")

Basic Attacks: Consume 1.66% Stamina and add 1% Stress

Specials: Consume 3.33% Stamina and add 2% Stress

Supers: Consume 1 Super Meter, 20% Stamina and add 25% Stress

[[Attack Upgrades]]
At 25%, 50%, and 75% Stress Meter: Bone Rush, Aerial Bone Throw, Blaster

At Phase 2: Almost every move is upgraded

ScarletHood is a Hemomancer, born with a curse to constantly bleed and manipulating his flowing blood to stay alive, refining it for his entire body.

Pop Friction and Nerve Twitch:
Movement option, scarlet slithers along the ground, having iframes as long as he slides, has a long endlag.


Charge Show:
Scarlet will stand in place and charge a small meter beside him, he can spend it on three moves via dropdown

Dexton Crusher: A powerful haymaker that gets stronger and slower the higher the charge, does equal to super damage at level 3.
Neuron Breaker: Dash attack that gets faster and slightly stronger per charge.

Stance move which puts you in Gun Stance, guns are chosen through dropdown and aimed via XYplot

Blood Uzi: Fire two bullets, can fire a max of 3 times.
Flesh Shotty: Shoot twice, a melee range burst of blood that deals high damage.
Bone Sniper: A ricochet bullet, needs to opt into the move before shooting.

Brain Launcher: Fires off brain as a homing projectile, explodes after hitting the opponent or a certain period of time passes.
Hand Buds: shoots off hands as mini assists that run around the screen and drill jump to attack.


Flesh of Prometheus:
Places a mound of guts onto the ground that deals Dps to the opponent while they're grounded, also gives a full blood cell instead of 1/2


Slight Twitch:
A long range combo move that gives you the scythe, changing your normal set and leaving you unable to use FingerGun and Spec Ops.

author: WouldYouPreferRam?
title: Slimegirl [A Bnnuy Update]
description:
Some goofy ahh slime girl just crawled out of the toxic waste bin. And then they [b]F...OUGHT![/b]

Slimegirl does very little contact damage [i](and I mean VERY little)[/i], however each hit comes with a good dosage of [b]POISON[/b]. Hustlers beware!


[hr][/hr]
[h2] What Do? [/h2]

Aura - Her aura is one of her greatest tools. It does [u]NOT[/u] add poison while the opponent is standing in it (unless overruled), but instead powers her poison and will effect some of her moves. The aura can change its size depending on a number of factors.

[Assimilate] - Any projectiles caught in her radius will be (or attempted to be) absorbed into Slimegirl, powering her poison for a duration and adding additional super for each projectile. This effect stacks the more its successfully used.

[Chernobyl] - Ignite all of Slimegirl's trails into burning acidic fire! This prevents Slimegirl from automatically making trails for a while, causing her friction to be absurdly high. If the opponent is [u]NOT[/u] in her radius, she will also strike them with a toxic beam wherever they stand.

[Meltdown] - Increased poison damage rate and damage in general while active. If the opponent stands in Slimegirl's radius during meltdown, they also take poison damage! Her radius is significantly smaller during meltdown and meltdown ends after a while or on hit.

[Melt] - Slimegirl warps to the first or last placed slimetrail, or lassail if that's out.

[Lassail] - Slimegirl throws her tail out like a lasso, carrying her toxic area with it.

[Snap Crackl Pop] - A projectile that works somewhat like Wizard's [Flame Wave]. The distance and speed at which it travels  is based on radius size

[Overdose] - Use more supers to pump more slime into the opponent, will take up to 8 extra supers!

[Venocache] - Have just a little too much poison? Cash it in for instant damage!

I've added [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3165815605&searchtext=codex] Character Codex [/url] support so check that out for a more in-depth explanation

Check out the [url=https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TyvrXHErrap9Bq0Tnahzx1vUBYxFU1yRae83CTQk_Ec/edit?usp=sharing] google doc [/url] for all the changes recorded in one neat place! [i]or don't that's fine too.[/i]
[hr][/hr]

(Anything currently in this mod is subject to be changed, modified, or removed so keep that in mind)

[h1](ALSO BE SURE TO CLEAR CHARACTER CACHE IN THE SETTINGS FIRST IF ANY PROBLEMS HAPPEN MKAY BYE!)

author: Zegawakun
title: SOTH - Immortal Flames (Version 1.601) 1.9.20 Update
description:
“A King who served his Kingdom” 
“Now roams the universe” 
“He is free, his soul at peace” 

This mod goes out to my brother who recently passed away.  We're continuing the story we started.  Me, my family, my friends, will always have him in our hearts, and as long as we have him in our memories, he will be forever immortal.
Rest in Peace Brother.  We love you.

Immortal Flames

Gameplay Concept 
-------
Immortal is a rush down character who uses the power of territories.  Territories strengthen his abilities to perform additional attacks which is beneficial to situation he may be in.  Territories powers up either his Offense, Defense, Speed, or Magic.  Use the correct territories and level up to max to perform optimal damage and combos.

Territories
-------
Territories are created by either using your “Flames of” specials, “Sun of” specials, or “I Claim This Land”.  Generating a territory creates a circle while inside, you gain benefits but also risk.  When you’re in your territory, depending on the type, you’ll gain points for leveling your types.  To reach max level, you need 1000 points.
If Immortal is in the territory alone unharmed, he will gain 2 points per tick.
If the opponent is in the territory alone unharmed, they will decrease the points by 1 per tick
If both Immortal and opponent are in the territory unharmed, Immortal will gain 1 point per tick.
The risk you both share while in the territory is the D.I. modifier for both is reduced by half. 

What you gain with levels is as follows:

Level 0: Nothing at all
Level 1 (250 points): Able to use Special corresponding to the type outside the territory.
Level 2: (500 points) Able to use Normal alt corresponding to the type outside the territory.
Level 3: (750 points) All risks are removed from the corresponding territory
Level 4: (1000 points) Gain all benefits you normally gain from being in territory, and more.

This page will be updated, but all the info is on the codex,  Please download Trimays Character Codex in the workshop!

Normals:
-------
When attacking the opponent, depending on the attack, you will be receiving 3% increase in your stats.  Ground Normals (excluding grab) have a different alts abilities depending on the territory Immortal is in or if they reached level 2.  These changes can increase the pressure onto the opponent.

Geranium Kick: Normal attack
Alt: Moves forward with a jump kick

Borage Ember: Normal mid move forward attack
Alt: Switch to a low, or a high damage high

Striped Volcano: Normal attack, immune to aerial attacks on initiative
Alt: Switch to high attack which is wider, or low attack, both loses aerial attack immunity

Rhododendron Sweep: Low attack which moves backwards
Alt: Switch to mid attack, which moves either back or forth

Tansy Eruption: Dash attack
Alt: Projectile immunity and burst are faster, takes longer to connect attack, or dash command grab

Sunflower Rise: Normal attack
Alt: Shoots a magic claw projectile

Oak Magma: Guard break
Alt: Creates 

Sage Kick: Jump attack
Alt: Dashes in the air, but only can attack aerial.  Projectile immunity

Aerials:
Magnolla Flames
Acanthus Cresent
Bay Tree Inferno
Belledonna Kick
Borage Ignite
Clematic EverGreen
Comlumbine Burn

Specials:
-------
To generate Territories, these abilities must be used.  Each has their own type of territory when used.  There are “Flames Of” for Ground, and “Son Of” for Aerial.  Once a territory is up with that type, you will no longer be able to use the ability again until the territory disappears.  

Enemy Engaged: If player is in territory, player can transfer territory to opponent as a Debuff.
Flames Of Offense: Two hit attack, creates Offense Territory
Flames of Defense: Armor then burst attack, creates Defense Territory
Flames of Speed: Dash attack, creates Speed Territory
Flames of Magic: Summon up to 5 meteors, creates Magic Territory
Sun of Offense: Downslash to ground, creates Offense Territory
Sun of Defense: Burst attack, creates Defense Territory
Sun of Speed: Dash attack, creates Speed Territory
Sun of Magic: Summon up to 4 flame butterflies, creates Magic Territory

Other specials can only be activated while being in the corresponding territory or by being level 1 with in the corresponding type.

Inferno Dragon: DP
Meteor Sphere: Shoots out projectile
Lava Rush: Teleports in front with the following options
Lava Slash: Slashes in front, up or down (cost 1 super meter)
Lava Finish: Jump Attack
Earthquake: OTG, very slow attack, but goes faster when opponent is on ground.  Creates an earthquake if Immortal is on the ground and misses the opponent.

Supers:
-------
I Claim This Land (Cost: 1): Creates a territory of your choosing in the spot you’re located
Enemy Invading (Cost: 1): When opponent is in a territory you’re not in, teleport anywhere within the territory
I Have Learn (Cost 2): 4 additional attacks which have a familiar sight.  Hitting the opponent with any of these attacks based on their type gains  5%. Debuffs opponent on hit based on type.
The Enemy Is Here (Cost 3): Gives the opponent a debuff which is based off the types.  The risk Immortal Flames gets when in his territory now applies to the opponent.  This also increases Immortal Flames points by 1 per tick based on the type of debuff, lasting 250 ticks.  This debuff timer is decreased by 25 ticks if the opponent hits
Sun Unite (Cost:4): Moves forward while blocking

Story:
-------
Immortal was one of the Three Kings of the world, who served his people in order to stop the cult of darkness.  For the years it took, he and the assistance of the other two kings, Blue Reviver as Law, and Demonic Lord as Chaos, were able to stop the evil known as Chaotic Queen, Shadow King, and 1%.  With peace achieved, and the world safe from the Gods, he believed his title of King can be disowned, as he wishes to see the other possibilities of the universe.  He now travels though worlds and dimensions, and assisting the people he meets on his travels, and viewing the heroes who soon will save their planet.

Profile:
-------
Name: Dash Kanawaga
Race: Immortal
Gender: Male
Age: Unknown
Height: 6’0”
Likes: To led the people to victory, his people, his friends, and family
Dislikes: Corruption, Chaotic Queen, Geinsoo, Bad leaders.

Relationships:
-------
Sin Reviver: Knowing the history of Revivers, they tend to be corrupted by their mothers or misguided.  With how Blue Reviver changed, he hopes to do the same for this Reviver.
Space Jester: Was allies before Space Jester was reincarnated.  To this day, he blames Space Jester for not assisting him during the attack by Shadow Reviver, even tho Space Jester was in a wheelchair with broken legs and arms.
Record Future:  He senses multiple heroes within Record Future.  Heroes which have fallen, but will never falter.  As long as the Chaos weapon exist, good will triumph evil.
Weapon Dancer: No relationship towards the dancer, but sense a strange familiar towards Weapon Reviver.
Doll Princess: No relationship
The Dungeon: No relationship
Dandy Lion: No relationship
Chaotic Queen: Immortal was the 2nd hero who put her down.  He was hoping to never see this corrupted woman again.  He only feels pity for her imprinted goals.
Animal Reviver: He believes this child is far corrupted to convert to the side of good.  However, it doesn’t hurt to try.
Record Vainglory: No relationship
Meteor Hero: No relationship

Record Future

Gameplay Concept
----------------------
The introductory character to the Sins of Saga's pack! A speedy character with gameplay similar to certain platform shooters! Build up Charge with Charged Movements in order to unleash speedy Guard Breaks and High Pressure tools! Chain together familiar moves with the Skill Card mechanic! Close the distance on your opponent with speedy aerial movements by using your install!
...Just don't miss! Or you'll be in a world of hurt!


------------------------
Gimmick Explanation
-------------------------
Record Future has 3 main gimmicks to keep track of

Charge Level: You can gain up to 3 Charge Levels, By using (Charge) movements, you'll gain 1 Charge Level. Certain moves can only be done at certain Charge Levels. Using ANY Charge Move
uses up your Charge! You can guess your Charge level by looking at the Charge indicator in the UI! While you have Full Charge, your block advantage will be increased on timed attacks!

Skill Cards: You have 4 White Card Slots, and 1 Gold Card Slots! They're comprised of familiar Specials and Supers respectively!

Chaos Meter: Keep track of the Meter! If it runs out, you won't be able to use White Cards! So refresh using LOTW Replication!

author: Zegawakun
title: SOTH - Sin Reviver (Version 2.8522) 1.9.20 Update
description:
“The Title of the Creator” 
“Create the world in your image” 
“Set The Rules and call it your home” 

Sin Reviver 

Gameplay Concept 
-------
Reviver can create up to 4 Sins and use them to perform offenses actions and defensive plays. Reviver needs to place the Sins for extended combos or preset traps. Reviver can gain Heaven Stacks from Sins to power of their meter to activate Sinful Mode. Control the Sins to counter your opponent and control your opponent to victory.

Normal: 
------- 
Normal Slap: Quickest attack in Reviver's kit 
Radiant Slash: Dashes forward to attack 
Forbid Double Slash: Double Hit
Heaven Awaken: On Init, Aerial immune on F3. Invincible on hitting the opponent.
Forbid Slasher: Mid hit
Foot Stomp: Low hit
Forbid Over Swing: High Guard Break
Forbid Jump Slash: Jump attack, which puts the opponent into Aerial 
Fluffy Kick: Aerial
Sinful Wings: Aerial
Aerial Swing: Upswing 
Aerial Down: Downswing 
Whirlwind: Spin attack which allows Sin Reviver to move in any direction, with hyper armor on the first spin.  On hitting the opponent, follow the opponent 
Heaven Awaken Up: Invincible on hitting the opponent.  Cannot use Heavens Awaken Up and Heavens Awaken Down once used until Sin Reviver lands 
Heaven Awaken Down: Invincible on hitting the opponent.  Cannot use Heavens Awaken Up and Heavens Awaken Down once used until Sin Reviver lands 

Special: 
--------- 

NOTE ABOUT SPECIALS:   
Reviver has 8 abilities called "Enlighten". Using most Normal Attacks will activate an "Enlighten" skill, which performs an attack with a unique property and summons a Sin.  This will also help with any punishment issue.  The following skills corresponds with the "Enlighten" abilities

Any Grab > Enlighten Blessing: Use Sin to cast Sky Drown.  Covers field which can summon Sins
Normal Slap > Enlighten Slap: Destroys "Fizzlable" projectiles and counters with homing projectiles.  Reviver can shoot a projectile which spawns a Sin at the end of the lifetime. Can attack mid or low
Radiant Slash > Enlighten Sun: Attacks far
Any Heaven Awaken > Enlighten Rain: Summons a Rain Cloud above the opponent.  While the opponent is under it, Reviver gains a buff to damage and hitstun.  Opponents increase their blockstun by 1. Also increase Heaven Stack by 5 each tick.
Forbid Double Slash > Enlighten Double: Armored attack.  Can dash.
Forbid Slasher > Enlighten Cross: Backdash with aerial immunity
Foot Stomp > Enlighten Dance: Teleports to attack
Forbid Over Swing > Enlighten Earthquake: Ground attack, guard break if close. Can dash but disables earthquake and Guard Break.
Forbid Jump Slash or Aerial Swing/Down > Enlighten Angel: Teleports to aerial opponent

Summon Sin: Creates a Sin.  
Surprise Attack (COST:400) : Summons a Sin on 3f, when spawn, they will attack depending on their command.
Together Now (COST:600) : The next Sin Ability can be used to attack at the same time you perform another action.

NOTE ABOUT SINS:   
If a Sin is attacked, they are stun for 50 frames, 2nd hit will make them disappear
If they are too far away from their Reviver during idle, they will follow them unless Reviver is in hurt state, then they will disappear
Lose 200 heaven stacks when a Sin disappears, only if Heaven Stack is above 1000

Follow: Control 1 Sin to follow either Reviver or opponent 
Sin Forward Slash: Quick attack! RANGE 40
Sin Big Slash: Pushes opponent either up, down, or mid.  Can hit OTG on bottom hitbox RANGE 30
Sin Multi Slash: For multi hit attack.  If blocked, it will interrupt RANGE 5
Sin Shield: Blocks hittable projectile and fires a projectile RANGE 15

Super: 
-------- 
Lead To Rebel: COST 2: Follow command but for multiple sins
Forsaken Wind: COST 2 Charges spin attack towards opponent for 45 frames.   Must be hit or blocked 2 times before interrupted
Sin Block: COST 2: Moves Sin to block (RANGE:10).  Blocking starts on 4f and ends at 11f.  If blocking next to Reviver, Reviver gains hyper armor.  Will counter if hit. Anything projectiles which are "fizzable" in it's hitbox will be converted into homing projectiles.  Grabbing Reviver will unblock the Sin.
Heaven Pride Sky Drown: COST 3: Giant aerial attack
Heaven Envy Nectars Hope: COST 3 (1 if in combo): Reviver and Sin 4 frame switch and Sin will explode.  Reviver will recovery instantly
Revive The Sins: COST 3: Reviver creates baby Sins.  On hitting the opponent, getting hit and parried, it creates a Sin.
Wings of Protection: COST 1: Reviver can repel the opponent
Sinful mode: When Reviver Heaven Stack meter is max, Reviver can enter "Sinful Mode".  During Sinful Mode, damage is increased, all “Enlighten” attacks (excluding Blessing) can be used without conditions, and Reviver can perform an attack while controlling the Sins at the same time.  Sinful Mode lasts for 44 to 400 ticks.  Sinful Mode timer goes down faster depending on the lack of Sins on the field.  Make sure you have all 4 out before activating the mode for max output.  You cannot summon Sins during this mode except by "Revive The Sin"

Defense:
----------
Sin Step: Cost 200 Heaven Stacks. Dashes forwards. Immune to projectile on 2f to end.  Projectile Immune lingers for 7 ticks
Help Me: If OTG, switches places with a Sin and they will explode
Talk: Now has interactions towards certain characters.  Choose Blue for kid personality, and Red for logical personality.  Some interactions may trigger the 3rd personality.

Story:
-------

Reviver is the newest reincarnation of the creator “The Queen”, with the same image as the original creator’s last child.  The creator's purpose is to create a world to their image. Each creator wishes to also involve their own Sins which represent the creator’s children in their plans.  Their Sins mean no harm, yet with the power they possess humanity feared and destroyed them.  This caused the creator grief and began to seek revenge upon what they created. 
Each timeline, each creator followed the same process and was defeated by either the hero of that timeline, or by the Record Future. 
Reviver had different plans for their creation.  They would not create a world with humanity, but a world only for their and other Sins.  Their creation will all look the same with an image of a fluffy angel creature, so every Sin would be equal.  The Reviver's only fear is if anyone invades their world and does them harm.

Personality:
--------

Two personalities come from Reviver.  If Reviver is interacting with a Sin, their bowtie will turn blue, showing the personality of a child, who just wants to have fun or sleep.  Yet otherwise, the bowtie will turn red, showing Reviver’s logical side, which keeps the world maintained.  Reviver is a caution child which doesn’t trust anyone but the Sins around them.  Their Sins share the same feeling as the Reviver, in which case whatever Reviver feels or thinks is also what the Sins feel and think. 

Profile:
---------

Name: Zegawa 
Race: Humanoid Soul 
Gender: Unknown 
Age: 6 
Height: 2’ 11” 
Likes: Fluffy Creatures, Circles, Spheres 
Dislike: Record Future, Circles or Spheres that comes in pairings 

Relationship:
--------

Record Future: Reviver fears the Record Future, as Record Future is the destroyer of most corrupt creators.  Reviver will not hesitate to strike first if Record Future appears in their world. 
The Dungeon: (no relation as of yet) 
Space Jester: Space Jester reveals the timelines of each of the creator's destruction to Reviver.  This raises Reviver’s paranoia, which was Space Jester’s intent for entertainment.
Weapon Dancer: Reviver sees the Weapon Dancer's partner as another them, which conflicts their thoughts of the world around them. Also Weapon Dancer makes a lot of attempts to adopt them
Immortal Flame: Reviver has a memory of him.  Something deep like they had known him for a long while. 
Chaotic Queen: Reviver sees them as their mother past self, but knows she’s filled with hate and evil.

Gameplay Concept
-------
Space Jester has the ability to control the opponent like a puppet.  Move your opponent using portals and space magic.  Space Jester can create up to 4 portals which he can use hand signs to attack or defend.  Be careful of your resources when casting your magic.  Make sure you place your portals and black hole correctly or your opponent will have the upper hand.

----
Normal Special Properties:

EYES!!!: Fastest attack 4f
Here, watch this: On successful first hit, will move forward
Flick your brat to Space: Low attack
I have an id..OH GOD: OTG Break Armor
Drinks On You: 3 hit
Beat You with An Idiot: Guard break
Yes My Child: Hits opponent up
17: Armor break
Dat A HitbBox : Aerial
Look at DAT ASS: Hits opponent down
6 Feet: Follows opponent if they’re in air
Jack NO!!! : Up Aerial
Hello There: Pulls opponent in when they are HurtAerial.  Cost Air Options

----
Specials:
----
Space Jester main gimmick is creating portals and using them for attack and defense.  Max of 4 portals can exist on the field.  The opponent is the only one who can go through the portal as long as they are not HurtGrounded.
Portal Stacks are form every 300 ticks.  If Space Jester hits the opponent with melee attacks, he decreases the cooldown for a Space Portal by 20.
Knives are not rechargeable.  Use them wisely.

There are 5 ways to create portals.

Making a Portal: Uses one Portal Stack to create a portal which can perform 4 different abilities
Making TWO Portals: Uses one Portal Stack to create two portals.  You can set the portal farther than "Making a Portal"
Slashing a Portal: If this attack hits the opponent (even parry), two portals are created.  Vertical portals are created while in air, while Horizontal portals are created while grounded
Knifing a Portal: Uses one Knife Stack to throw a knife, which after 4 ticks, will create a portal which can perform 4 different abilities
Using Any Ground Movement Options: An option will appear to create a portal near you and your opponent by using Dash Forward, Dash Backward, or Jumping.  This will create a Blue Portal which cannot be used for hand gestures and will expire in 120 ticks.

Abilities for portals:
There are 4 abilities Space Jester can do while a portal exists.  Abilities varies on the portals vertical and horizontal positioning

Flick: 
Horizontal: Quick flick attack
Vertical: If aiming up, launches the opponent up.  If aiming down, slams opponent to grounded.

Grab:
If it hits the target, it will stop their momentum


Block:
Horizontal: Any attack that hits this hand will be counter with a slash projectile
Vertical: While Space Jester is near this hand, gain hyper armor

Shoot: 
Horizontal: Shoots a space snot which if it hits the opponent
Vertical: Spawns a projectile on the opponent

----
Super:
----
Move My Puppet: COST 2 - Can apply small force to the opponent in any direction
Where I throw my Junk:  COST 2 -Creates a black hole where everything near it will be dragged in.
Name This Laser: COST 3 - All portals will shoot a laser.  If there is a black hole, it will also shoot out 4 lasers.
I'm An Artist: COST 3 - Command Grab, with an interesting twist (interactions up to 101 characters)

Side Abilities:

Profile:

Gender: Male
Age: Unknown
Height: 5ft 8'
Likes: Space Neo, His Tusk Guardians, causing chaos and having fun, seeing how far his space magic really can become, creating new insane methods of madness and insanity

Story:
-------
Space Jester is the reincarnation of the previous Renjin from the Saga world. He was a member of the Chaos Guardians until he went to seek the truth about his past.  The action was forbidden, which made Space Jester an outlaw of the Chaotic world. After discovering his past, he had nothing to return to until the one fateful night he was found by the God of Space.   The God bestow him the power of his magic to Space Jester and became the god’s companion and right-hand man. Til this day, Space Jester has served the God and their life long companion.
As of now, Space Jester has been focusing his entertainment on Record Future, who’s goal is to convert the creators to good, or eliminate them.  Space Jester tends to make Record Future’s job a little difficult.

Personality:

Space Jester’s previous personality was quiet and yet serious about the task he was given as a Chaos Guardian.  After he was taken in by his God, he has developed a chaotic face.  His love for the chaos, the sheer thrill and random nature of the universe. He's incredibly loyal to his God and assist him with entertainment by causing chaos and luring in new victims to the gods Circus Realm. He can be friendly or pure evil, the mood varies.

Relationship:

Weapon Dancer: Space Jester tries to avoid or irritated the Weapon Dancer and his partner Weapon Reviver.  Space Jester has a feeling he knows at least the partner Weapon Dancer travels with.
The Immortal: One of the few Space Jester respects. This figure Jester will not disrespect.
The Queen: Space Jester just sees her as another reincarnation of the first creator.  Space Jester crack jokes about her being the Final Boss in every timeline.

author: Vale of a Thousand Cats
title: Spellblade [0.10.5]
description:
[h1] Latest update: 0.10.5[/h1]
Lots of fixes, balance updates and some new specials are here! One for each element, but are subject to change! I can confirm the next major patch will be 1.0.0, which'll have the hero skin!!!!

[h1]Spellblade: The Runic Duelist[/h1]
[b]Spellblade[/b] is a versatile stance character that can activate different runes to change their game-plan on the fly. Pressure opponents or they'll suffer high damage from mistakes with [b]Fire[/b]. Keep enemies on their toes through traps and keep-away tactics with [b]Ice[/b]. Rush down your foe and don't give them any breathing room with [b]Shock[/b]. Control and adapt to the situation on the fly with each of these Runes that can be used at any time!

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Spellblade is now at the point where I want to get as much feedback and testing as possible! He's targeting vanilla character balance, and any and all feedback is appreciated!

Spellblade also has [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3165815605]Codex support[/url]! Use this to read up on individual moves and for an overall guide on the character.

Check the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/discussion/3255990116/4328601129275217015/]thread below[/url] for information on the Hero skin!

[h3]Mechanics[/h3]
Spellblade has access to three special move runes. Using a rune fills up the charge bar with the respective element. While Spellblade has any element charge, they gain access to the respective element specials and a unique passive effect for each element:

[b]Fire Passive:[/b] Dealing damage with sword attacks applies a small stacking burn over time.
[b]Ice Passive:[/b] Dealing damage with sword attacks builds up a freezing effect on the opponent.
[b]Shock Passive:[/b] Grants access to a short 5f dash that keeps momentum after.

While using an element, Spellblade also has access to the following:

[b]Ruin:[/b] A UI toggle that causes automatic follow-ups on the selected move.
[b]Boost:[/b] A slightly delayed aerial dash that goes towards the opponent, costing charge.
[b]Cycle:[/b] An extra UI based move that can switch to another element at the cost of 100 charge.
[b]Dispel:[/b] An extra UI based move that dispels the current element, removing all charge.

Spellblade is at his best when in an element, especially the element best suited to the current situation! However, Spellblade does have some tools outside of an element, such as Blink Dart, a dagger that sticks to whatever it hits and allows them to teleport to it when in range!

[h3]Supers[/h3]
[b]Surge: Fire, Ice and Shock (Level 1):[/b] Three different attacks, one for each element, that cycles to the next one whenever used. 
[b]Memoria (Level 1):[/b] A unique super that stores the last used "Spell" to be used in conjunction with another move in the future.
[b]Omnislash (Level 3):[/b] A command grab finisher that has high minimum damage and multiple hits.
[b]Surge: Rune (Level 4):[/b] Enables all three runes at the same time, granting access to all specials and passive effects. The charge bar will drain over time.

Thank you to everyone who's supported me throughout the development of Spellblade that helped me get to this point! Every idea, bit of feedback, or just general conversation has motivated me to continue working on him. Thank you, truly!

Upcoming content (no particular order):
[list]
[*]Hero skin (1.0.0)
[*]VFX and visual polish
[*]Sound effect pass
[*]Feedback based balance
[*]Various fixes
[*]Move reworks/updates
[/list]

description:
Springtrap FNaF as a "hustler"

Let me know what you think of this character
I have no idea what I'm doing

Phantom Meter:
There are four moves that use the phantom meter. The Meter has three segments, and takes 600 frames to fill completely.

Phantoms:
Phantoms uses one segment of the phantom meter to summon a phantom. They all do different things, but most of them control space.

EX Phantoms and Super Phantoms:
Uses two and three segments of the Phantom Meter respectively. Different levels of phantoms can have wildly different effects. for example, Shadow Bonnie simply jumps forward if used through Phantom, but will prevent the opponent from jumping if used through Super Phantom.

Monitors:
You can only have one monitor out at once. Activating it will make it flash, damaging the opponent. You can create permanent monitors placed on tables using meter.

Backroom:
A hard to land command grab that does massive damage. Uses four levels of meter.

Hocus Pocus:
Teleports you to Slasher. If Slasher is not out, then you will teleport in place.

Bite:
 Down throw while on ground, adds a bar of Phantom Meter.

Documentation and Phantom explanations can be found here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XTJ7tZOgqu6pKQHK1_2Bkoi3ZSlF65BdjO-bwSE1DrA/edit?usp=sharing

author: Beer
title: Susano'o
description:
[h1] Warning [/h1] 
This Character is a relic of old yomi and not very balanced at all
no i will not update it go away


I am strength, I am power, I am everything! My very being is the sword of the god that will destroy all! I am Takehaya Susanoo! …the end has come.[b]I am strength, I am power, I am everything! My very being is the sword of the god that will destroy all! I am Takehaya Susanoo! …the end has come.[/b]

[h1] Susano'o joins Yomi Hustle[/h1]

This character's main gimmick is that you have a variety of powerful special moves, however you have to work to earn them.

This character's ui looks a little different
It's essentially supposed to be
Extra(movement/defense stuff), Super moves, Special moves, Drive moves, Normals

Use normals to move the gauge forwards and use Drive moves to unlock or level up the special move you want.

Make sure to structure your combos in a way that let's you unlock the best ones for your current situation

Here's a quick rundown of all of the special moves

[b] Sundering Claws[/b] 
this is the move you start out with, quite weak at level 1 however it is projectile invulnerable, at most you'll be able to jab out of it and continue the combo
level 2 goes much farther and has armor, while level 3 has all of the previous attributes but it launches the opponent at an angle that makes it easy to combo from

[b] Towering Flame[/b]
A very handy special to have, not only is it a great combo ender due to its high minimum damage but also it's straight up frame 1 invulnerable which means the opponent will have to think twice before coming that close to you

[b] Megalith [/b]  
This move is a handy OTG (off the ground) launcher it also gets to level up till level 3 where it'll have armor similar to sundering claws and even wallsplat opponents

[b] Hunter's Fang [/b] 
This is one of susanoos best special moves, allowing you to use it in mid air  aswell as being a great way to bring opponents back to the ground since susanoo is a ground fighter first.
Hunter's Fang level 2 will leave the opponents at a low angle letting you follow up with standing attacks.

[b] Dancing Dual Kick [/b] 
This move is also a great combo extender aswell as having a bunch of corner carry and hitting OTG , the opponent will always get sent high into the air though.

[b] Inevitable Calamity [/b] 
While being kinda bad in combos due to its extremely high scaling multihits this move is a great neutral tool due to it's super fast 2 frame startup, allowing you to beat even grabs up close.

[b] Splintering Thrust.. aka GODPRESS[/b]
is your opponent blocking too much how about you command grab them and slam them into the nearest wall, for a free combo extend, reminder that you can only use this move once per combo.

[b] Blade of Judgement [/b]
Arguably one of susano'os best specials not only does it have very long range and launches easily, it also gives susanoo access to a new super, being an even stronger version of the blade.

[b] That's pretty much it for all the specials but here are some extra things to keep in mind.. [/b]
Susano'o has 3 supers

Unchained 
This super while costly is definitely worth 6 bars as it unlocks all your special moves at level 1

Bloodspiller
aka the DUNK this is your main combo ender for cheap bars

Strike of the Possessed God
This super works in a weird way
Susanoo will do all his available special moves and then follow it up with a giant mouth laser, if you have barely any specials unlocked this move isn't really worth it, however the more specials you have unlocked the higher and higher the damage becomes so use your meter wisely!

author: WouldYouPreferRam?
title: Tale (Fairytale Remake)
description:
The shady "Tale Fairy" re-enters Your Only Move Is Hustle with all new equipment! Using various moves from different fairytales, fables and other related stories, she can successfully cover her real identity and hide her illegal weapons from the feds.

TECHNICALLY, I'm remaking the first mod I've ever made, since the original Fairytale mod sprites and ideas came from me and all the coding stuff was done by @Miyuukitsune at the time. Now I can actually make the characters I want to make, so I revisited Fairytale.

----THE DIFFERENCE----
- Tale skips instead of dash on the ground
- Items from [Basket Case] are truly randomized now, but can be copied as the next NEXT item or recycled for super, discarding it.
- Not every item can be queued, and items that have been queued cannot be queued again until the current item is different by any means
- Tale can detonate "bombs", which will also buffer her current move
- Tale has a lot more multi-hitting moves than usual
- Most (not all) ammo shot from her weapons can be aimed using DI
- Tale uses modified Cowboy bullets. If you are used to his bullets then the knowledge should carry over

----ITEM DESCRIPTIONS----
- CLUB: Basic item that deals standard damage and hitstun
- SPADE: Multi-hitting card that hits up to 8 times. Defies gravity and cannot be parried
- HEART: Heals Tale on hit but has horrific hitstun and high air friction.
- DIAMOND: Applies a lot of hitlag on hit but near zero hitstun
- APPLE: Adds 100f of poison to the opponent on hit, bounces off the floor
- GRENADE: Explodes near the opponent or after enough bounces. Can bounce off all surfaces. Can be detonated
- BRICK: Relatively high damage and minimum damage, can hit opponents from knockdown
- LANDMINE: Explodes when hit by anything. Once it lands, it also explodes if it detects anything hostile. Can be detonated
- DOUBLOON: Can reflect Tale's bullets based on DI if the bullet connects. Bounces off all surfaces with very low gravity. It can also hit the opponent while it's active
- FIREWORK: Starts slow then ramps in speed. Will explode near the opponent. Can be detonated
- BOOK: Homes in on the opponent dealing basic damage on hit. Has high air friction.
- LOG: Hitting the opponent bounces the log towards Tale. Will despawn after 5 hits or some amount frames. Will bounce off all surfaces 99 times
- CRATE: Explodes after it hits the opponent or has been hit twice while airborne deploying your current item and adding ammo. Hitting it will knock it away. Can be detonated. Has more value when recycled.
- HAY: Bounces along the ground, will deal high knockback when hitting the opponent

Special Cards can only be added to the item queue when certain conditions are met. Recycling these will always reward more super meter

The respective gold cards are given when Alice despawns peacefully.
- GOLD CLUB: Increased damage and meter gain on hit
- GOLD SPADE: Hits 12 times instead of 8 and can bounce off all surfaces. Increased damage
- GOLD HEART: Increased healing, damage, and lower gravity. Bounces off walls
- GOLD DIAMOND: Increased hitstun and damage. Bounces off the floor

(Literally anything in this mod is subject to change at any point as I plan to add more in the future)

author: myers
title: The Cursed Lawyer
description:
~ Higuruma Hiromi ~
yes another (and probably my only) jjk mod

my first mod and took way too long to make

obviously not perfect, so feedback and stuff is appreciated

his domain has four  rulings: Not Guilty, Guilty, Guilty w/ Confiscation, and Death Penalty



- - - - -
Not Guilty: returns to his normal stance, reverts his stats, and undoes confiscation (sucks to suck)
- - - - -
Guilty: higuruma gets an attack/defense buff
- - - - -
Guilty w/ Confiscation: same as guilty but you deplete all of the other player's meter and prevent them from gaining more
originally i wanted it to remove just Supers, but idk how to do that
- - - - -
Death Penalty: Same as confiscation, but you get the executioner's sword. Including an instant-kill super and music options.
- - - - -

domain ruling is dependent on rng and your hp. the better the ruling (for you) the lower the chance, but as your health drops, those chances increase while the chances of Not Guilty and Guilty decrease.

his domain costs 1 level, but it also has a 300 tick cooldown, which is 5 seconds. which doesnt seem long, but is actually kinda long ingame
if it gets canceled early, the cooldown is 150 ticks (2.5 seconds), the 300 tick is after a successful domain
yes, it supports domain clashing
his domain uses migues' base domains

he also has a Reversed Cursed Technique super, which does what it does, but after two uses he depletes his output and burns it out.

which leads into Black Flash.

he has a very very very low chance to land a Black Flash with one of his non-gavel related normal attacks. Black Flashes are variants of the same attack that deal more damage, give extra meter and reduce the current domain cooldown. The first Black Flash increases the chance for the 2nd Black Flash. Upon landing the second one (and every subsequent one), everything prior mentioned occurs, but you also regain one (1) RCT charge. This Black Flash also increases the odds for the next one. The 3rd and on Black Flashes all do the same as the 2nd one, minus increasing the odds any further. My record in an actual match is 3 consecutive
He has an Evidence bar now, which increases upon landing certain attacks and black flashes. the higher the evidence, the better the odds for domain and the higher the chance of black flashes.
Getting it to orange changes the system into 70% confiscation and 30% death penalty, and red gives you 100% death penalty.
A succsessful domain will reset the evidence resource (however due to a visual bug you have to land a move that updates it to update the visual)
Although you are not guaranteed to land any in every match, so don't rely on them too much.
And the Black Flash damage buff is stacked on top of the Guilty ruling attack buff, so those hurt.

[h1] King of Curses mod: [/h1]
https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3261065305
(confiscation takes the kamutoke)
Gavel Whip animation done by LuiXee as well

New Death Penalty animations for King of Curses, Disgraced One, Sukuna, Vessel, and Reincarnation

Gut-Check has a slightly higher Black Flash chance.

please leave balance / move suggestions, bugs, and the like in the comments, he could probably really use them

author: Vermilingus
title: The Machine - BETA
description:
This character is still very much in beta, expect some things to be unfinished or in flux.
Don't expect to be winning many tournaments with this guy right now.
Preview image definitely not final, will add when sprites are fully finalised.

BREAKDOWN:

UNIVERSAL MOVES:
MOVEMENT - Machine's Movement works differently to other characters; it is momentum-based. This means it can take a little bit to slow down if you need to.
AIR ACTIONS - Machine's air actions do not reset on landing; instead they reset over time.
BOOST DASH - Machine's unique dash is the Boost Dash, which uses an air action to do a quick, invincible dash. This is usable both on the ground and in the air.
SLIDE - An attack which starts the Machine's slide - the fastest long distance movement option the Machine has.
STOMP - A fast fall which allows Machine to conserve its momentum while changing direction. It also works as an attack, but you have to be precise with it.

NORMALS:
FEEDBACKER - A quick jab with the feedbacker arm. Punches back projectiles at the opponent
LOW WHIP - SWEEP THE LEG. Hard knockdowns on hit.
KNUCKLE BLASTER - A two-hit armored explosive punch which sends enemies flying.
WHIPLASH - Every game is better with a grappling hook. Launch towards your opponent on hit!
WHIPLASH PULL - It's like whiplash, but, well, pulls the enemy.

SUPERS:
ELECTRIC RAILCANNON (Level 2): A slow, long range, powerful 360 degree shot which scales very quickly with coins.

REVOLVER STANCE: The revolver is a quick, balanced weapon, allowing Machine to play a dynamic neutral game.
MARKSMAN - Fires a quick shot with full 360 aim.
KNEECAPPER - A quick low shot which also lets the Machine retreat and leaves it in the air
PIERCER - Fires a fast traveling shot which pierces through enemies.
IRON HAIL (Air Only) - Fires 1-3 shots downwards
PISTOL WHIP - Pistol whip the next person who says "shenanigans"
THROW COIN - Pings a coin into the air.
COIN BOUNCE - Bunts a coin upwards, amplifying its damage.
SHARPSHOOTER - Fires off a fast, bouncing shot which gets stronger if you ricochet it off the walls.

SUPERS:
EMERGENCY STASH (Level 1) - Throws a coin regardless of how many you have stocked.
MAKE IT HAIL (Level 2) - Throws all coins you have available
SLAB REVOLVER (Level 1) - A quick, hitscan projectile

COINS:
Coins are the Revolver's signature mechanic. You can hold up to four at a time and they regenerate over time.
If you shoot a coin which is in the air with your Revolver, it becomes a Ricoshot.
A ricoshot will target any other coins in the air, gaining damage as it does so.
When there are no coins left, the Ricoshot will target either a Core Eject or an Enemy, prioritising Core Ejects.
The Ricoshot does not care who created the coins.

SHOTGUN STANCE: The Shotgun is a close range, higher damage weapon allowing for a stronger combo game.
FIREWORKS - A two hitting combo extender from Shotgun Stance
WEDDING CRASHER - A forward facing shotgun blast that knocks opponents far away and wallsplats.
PARTY POPPER - an anti-air shotgun blast.
VOLUME BUMP - a gap closing launching hit
CORE EJECT - Lob an explosive projectile from your shotgun. When hit by a Marksman shot or a Coin Ricochet the explosion is amplified. CAUTION: Core eject can damage The Machine.
PUMP CHARGE - Pump the shotgun to increase the damage, hitstun and range it can do, but be sure not to pump it too much or it will explode on you when you try to fire it.
JACKHAMMER - Slug your opponent with the Jackhammer, doing increasing damage based on how fast you are moving. Hit it at max speed for heavy damage and knockback (Warning: Jackhammer will need to cooldown after a fully charged hit)

SUPERS:
ULTRA PUMP (Level 3): For a period of time, this move locks your Pump Charge to Level 3. Blast away!

NAILGUN STANCE:
SWEEPER: A burst of nails sweeping from low to high
METAL FLOOD: a massive forward firing shot of nails, great for getting some distance on enemies.
FIRE MAGNET: Fire a magnet which stays where it hits. Fire nails near this magnet to create a growing cloud of damaging nails, which explode into a nail bomb at the end.
PLACE MAGNET: Put down a magnet wherever you want
OVERHEAT: RAIN: Use built up Heat to fire a barrage of nails into the air, where they'll come raining down.
ROBOTIC VIPER - An uppercut with a large hitbox that can be used as an anti-air or as a chunky combo hit
PINCUSHION - A dashing multihit thrust of the nailgun
OVERHEAT VIPER - A multihitting nail uppercut.
SAWBLADE - Fire a slow, bouncing, three hit projectile which can orbit Magnets.

ROCKET STANCE:
FIRE ROCKET: Fires... well, it fires a rocket. You can use the FREEZEFRAME toggle to pause it in midair
SRS CANNON: Fires a bouncing cannonball that explodes when shot
ROCKET RIDE: Ride one of your rockets to teach your opponents to love the bomb. (Hint: used most easily on frozen rockets). This doesn't need to be done in Rocket Stance but I've included it here anyway because it kinda needs it.
RISING FALCON: Soar into the sky to pluck your opponents out of the air and bring them crashing back down with a point-blank missile

BLOOD IS FUEL:
When The Machine hits an enemy, Blood Particles are spawned.
If The Machine collects a Blood Particle, it gains Super Meter. Without Blood, Machine has very low meter gain, so make sure you're getting in there and collecting that Blood!

WEAPON SWAPPING:
Selecting a weapon with the weapon UI above the move menu will change which weapon you're going to be using next turn - plan your moves in advance to set up!

STYLE, BABY
The Machine's damage is affected by the variety of moves you use, so play stylish, don't get hit, and use that whole moveset to push your damage multiplier up and up!

author: Vermilingus
title: The Senator
description:
Here to Make Yomi Great Again is the Senator! A semi-heavy grappler based around his Nanomachine mechanic, where he can build up armour to let him tank through hits or cash it out for dash cancels and enhanced moves to open up his combo game.
He's largely based around the ground game, forgoing long air combos and fancy sky trickery to slam the opponent into the ground and keep them there with chain grabs. The Senator has unique combo routes full of grabs and OTGs, giving his combos a unique flavour.

This is my first mod so constructive (read: CONSTRUCTIVE) criticism is welcomed and encouraged, I'm aware I'm not going to get everything right first try.

MOVESET

NORMALS
NO CONFIDENCE - a quick stomp that gives some plus frames, can give a combo off of an OTG hit
CONFIDENCE VOTE - A far reaching low stomp that creates a shockwave to blast opponents towards the Senator, regardless of which way they're DI'ing.
HARD DEBATE (Air OK) - a medium speed gut punch that's good for continuing combos. His fastest mid-range poke.
FUND RAISER (Air OK) - otherwise known as the Electric Wind Senator Fist. This is a launcher with pretty good travel distance that, if landing the sweetspot, leads to massive amounts of hitstun.
ABSOLUTE MAJORITY - His Guard Break move. A downward dunk punch that spikes enemies off the ground. Grants Nanomachines
IMPEACHMENT (Air ONLY) - A two-footed stomp which spikes enemies into the ground, allowing OTG pickups if low to the ground
APPROVAL FALL (Air ONLY) - a risky all-or-nothing elbow drop which leads to a knockdown on both you and the opponent but still allowing an OTG combo on hit. Grants Nanomachines
APPROVAL PLUMMET - An enhanced version of Approval Fall with better recovery and combo potential. Costs Nanomachines
BALLOT - The Senator's Chain Grab, Ballot leads into either of the following:
SPOILED BALLOT - A pop-up into punt kick which deals heavy damage and grants Nanomachines.
LIMITED BALLOT - A hard knockdown headbutt which leaves the opponent directly in front of the Senator, allowing for OTG combo extensions
ONE PARTY BALLOT - A devastating quintuple headbutt dealing heavy damage and allowing just as much combo as Limited Ballot. Costs Nanomachines
HARD DEBATE - A medium speed gut punch that's good for continuing combos.

OTHER SPECIALS
TOUGH BALLOT - A slower, longer range way into the Ballot Chain Grab, Grants Nanomachines. Can be used from Run-Off
POSTAL BALLOT (Air Only) - An air grab which slams opponents into the ground and puts them into the Ballot Chain Grab state.
DROP BOX (Air OK) - An anti air grab which slams opponents into the ground, allowing for OTG. Grants Nanomachines.
BOUNDARY LINE - A ground explosion that knocks enemies towards the Senator.
BOUNDARY SHIFT- A triple explosion that knocks enemies towards the Senator. Costs Nanomachines to use.
CONVINCING ARGUMENT - a Reversal Body Explosion which knocks enemies away from the Senator. Grants Nanomachines.
PAPER TRAIL - A shoulder tackle that knocks opponents back, or pops them up for a combo if hit on the Sweetspot at the beginning
AUDIT TRAIL - An enhanced version of Paper Trail with better combo potential and some invincibility frames. Costs Nanomachines

RUN OFF
Run off is a movement option which can either be done from neutral, or cancelled from other moves at the cost of Nanomachines.
From Run Off you have the following options:
CONTESTED RACE - A clothesline which leaves opponents in a knockdown state, able to be hit OTG.
DIRECT PRIMARY - A superkick which kills Senator's momentum and knocks opponents back
ABSOLUTE MAJORITY
DROP BOX
TOUGH BALLOT
BOUNDARY FAULT

SUPERS
JINGO BOOST (LEVEL 1) - Grants 100% Nanomachines
BOUNDARY CREEP (LEVEL 1) - A slow moving wall of fire which stops projectiles and makes for a safer approach for the Senator.
GERRYMANDERING (LEVEL 2) - Creates a line on the ground which becomes a massive damaging eruption after a delay. Has a hitbox on Senator's fist at the beginning, confirming the explosion if it hits and allowing it to be a potent combo extender.
AIRTIGHT ARGUMENT (LEVEL 3) - A massive body explosion which deals heavy damage and knocks opponents flying into the air.
SEAT OF OFFICE (LEVEL 3) - An OTG only command grab which deals heavy damage by barraging the opponent with a massive rush of punches.

description:
The SOLDIER (Cloud Strife) Breaks his Limits in YOMI Hustle!

The SOLDIER excells and close quartes combat using his massive sword to his advantage. He is a close to medium range character focused on high pressure, playing around his big sword and his limit break mechanic, allowing him to go beyond some of his attacks regular properties to become even better!

Limit is charged over the course of the match by deal or taking damage, a little extra from landing different specials and from landing one of his guard breaks. Once limit is charged and ready, he will begin to glow as he is ready to enhance one of his specials or supers into their Limitbroken variation, gaining significantly increased damage and some additional properties.

Enjoy a fast paced, big sworded character from the world of Final Fantasy 7

Special thanks to the members of YomiC who helped me bring this character together, and special thanks to
Lankes: for his help on Ascension, Swipe and the idle
