author: LuiXee
title: The True Hero - Undyne/Undyne the undying
description:
Undyne from undertale, a zoner with an upperhand in mid ranged trades.
-she starts with 0 determination, you gain it by hitting the opponent with multiple attacks, this increase depends on how long your combo is, crit bar, how much hp difference there is (having lower hp than your opponent increases determination per hit and having more hp you gain less) spears also apply for these effects,you can use once of two supers, depending on your playstyle: defensive or agressive (PROTECT or PUNISH). these start draining determination to get truehero %. For example if you chose to increase your defense, you gain some extra effects but lose dmg, and vice versa. if you get 100% truehero you turn into UNDYING next time you are hit.
-Blue spears: you can set spears to throw them later, these spears increase determination by 2 + combo hits and do more dmg than yellow spears, the limit is 5
-Yellow spears: you can throw them and change it's direction mid air, it's really fast and won't dissapear until it hit's the opponent 2 times (including the throw)
[h1]PROTECT[/h1]
you gain defense and lose damage, your spears are now stronger, having more dmg and -1 proration,
[h1]PUNISH[/h1]
you gain dmg but lose defense, you also get + frames on some moves and lose - frames on others, pretty simple, this dmg boost doesn't seem like much until you land good combos. risk and reward
[h1]UNDYING[/h1]
in the undying state your attacks do a bit of more dmg and have more range by default, blue spears limit increases to 7 and yellow spears limit increases to 3, the counter effect from PROTECT or PUNISH reduces drastically, if you chose PROTECT you'll heal double, the spears will turn bigger and will have more dmg too, if you chose PUNISH the lower defense won't only dissapear but you'll gain a little bit of defense..

-Crit Bar mechanic: it's constantly increasing, if you use an attack and hit, you'll get more determination the closer it is to the center, if you get a crit (48% to 52%) you get the most determination and also get a little bit of true hero%, you can see it under undyne
-Green Soul/ Special Green Attack: a super that costs 3 bars and 10 determination (on truehero it doesn't), combo only. It resets opponent's momentum each 10 ticks. while the opponent is on green soul state you spawn spears on their position excepting for yellow spears. Green Soul state lasts for 120 ticks

author: LimboKid
title: Trix User
description:
The alien changeling makes his way into Yomi Hustle!

This mod adds in the Trix User, the powerful wielder of a strange alien device that is capable of turning them into all sorts of strange and unique alien lifeforms.

Certain transformations are "permanent", meaning that you stay as that species until you choose to detransform.

Other transformations are "temporary", meaning that you'll really only see them for a move or two, usually ones that go chained together, these transformations can be blink and you'll miss it at times, but what matters is that they get to show off their cool abilities while proving to be a major obstacle for the enemy and tripping them up with all the quick-switching between alien life forms.

Finally, certain species are simply too powerful to be kept as either or, and as such, they've been labeled "super" transformations, these require meters to be used and will usually be utilized for an incredibly strong or useful move before going away once more.

(some other more minor features the character has/will have by the end)
- a life preservation failsafe that will trigger one time per match, if and when the user is attacked after getting to  15% health (not yet implemented)
- a Master Control super, responsible for allowing the usage of the "temporary" transformations and quick-switching between aliens (implemented)
- customizable Omnitrix and eye color (associated with custom color 01 and 02 of your personal style, also implemented)

author: Nuion
title: Umbra
description:
Umbra is a character that uses an Umbrella as weapon and petal magic to fight.

Her playstyle revolves around her defensive projectiles that allow you to have defensive options when approaching or getting hit. She has some fancy supers using her petal magic that allow you to deal massive damage or fancy combos.

This is my first ever character, I never did any kind of spriting nor drawing before this. Everything is done from scratch and as clean as I was able to make it.

She was one of the first ever modded characters for YomiHustle that was completed. She is an og.

If you want to see more cool characters, join the community and see some Work In Progress content of talented creators or just contact me, join the Discord here: https://discord.gg/MjxbWrHQNA

[b]Moveset[/b]


[b]Normals[/b]

[b]Sting[/b] Fast jab, good in neutral
[b]Low Bud[/b] Decently fast, low  (HAS SWEETSPOT)
[b]Swing[/b] Bread and butter attack, has good damage (HAS SWEETSPOT)
[b]Tripple Thorn[/b] Triple Hit, strong sweetspot  (HAS SWEETSPOT)
[b]Sprout[/b] Uppercut, 2 hits, can be cancelled on first hit
[b]Glaive[/b] Ranged Multihit attack, DI Mixup
[b]Wind Slide[/b] Floor Slide, pretty fast, good to carry people to corners
[b]Season Grab[/b] Command Grab, has 2 options
-> [b]Next Season[/b] High Frame advantage, low damage, is a combo extender
-> [b]Season End[/b] Instantly Knocks down, high damage, combo finisher

[b]Normals Air Only[/b]

[b]Single Thorn[/b] Upward attack, good damage and hitstun (HAS SWEETSPOT)
[b]Flower Split[/b] Short range attack, can hit OTG (on the ground)
[b]Downpour[/b] Downward attack, knocks enemy towards ground (HAS SWEETSPOT)


[b]Specials[/b]
[b]Wind Dash[/b] Short Range dash with hitbox
[b]Seeker[/b] Delayed projectile aiming at enemy
[b]Razor Petal[/b] Defensive Projectile, follows Umbra around, can only have 2 active 
[b]Flying Wind[/b] Dashes Forward, creates hitbox behind, slow version outside combo
[b]Blinking Wind[/b] Same as Flying Wind, but faster and only available in combo
[b]Storm Stance[/b] Activate Storm Stance, ignores gravity/velocity and holds you in place, allows one out of 3 follow 
up attacks
->  [b]Breeze[/b] Fast, Short Ranged, Low Damage (good minimum damage)
->  [b]Gust[/b] Medium, Medium Ranged, Medium Damage (good minimum damage)
->  [b]Gale[/b] Slow, LongRanged, High Damage (good minimum damage)


[b]Supers[/b]

[b]Petal Slap (1bar) [/b] big diagonal hitbox, resets enemy speed on hit, has couple frames of invincibility
[b]Petal Dance (3bar)[/b] Big Multihit High Damage super

author: WouldYouPreferRam?
title: Vampire
description:
The unholy duo, Vamp & Ire have arrived to tag-team the competition!

Vamp is a puppet character that has a few grapples in her kit. If you enjoy cool command grabs, this hustler is for you. If you enjoy puppet characters, this hustler is practically MADE for you! (not really)

---Special Moves List---
Moves that have special properties that aren’t immediately noticeable

[Quick Step] - Dash forward at breakneck speeds hitting the opponent in the process. Higher distance = Slower startup

[Call Ire] - Enables the use of Ire in battle. Ire is a lighter version of Vamp with the ability to fly. She can do different attacks based on the attacks Vamp does. Some of Ire’s attacks require a direct order (using a turn).

[Crossbow] - Fire a wooden stake to pierce through the opponent. The crossbow itself has a hitbox as well.

[Torpedo] - Dive down head-first in one of five directions, taking the opponent with you along the way, and landing to deal the final blow.
Consumes 2 super; available when high in the air

[Drag/Crash] - Drag the opponent across the stage throwing them Forwards, Backwards, or Downwards at the end. If done at certain heights, hitting the ground will deal extra damage.

[Steel Spike] - Summon a large spike at the opponent that can point in one of 4-directions and can be moved slightly left or right. The spike has a dangerous tipper, keep that in mind. Only one spike can be out at a time, however this attack can be done regardless as it has its own hitboxes on Vamp’s wings.

[Whiplash] - Release a large whip to grab the opponent and slam them on the ground. Afterwards you can choose one of 6 directions (or slam again if you have at least 1 super bar) to throw the opponent.

[Bite/Reel] - Use your opponent as fuel for your attacks, trading the opponents hp for super meter! Once you’ve used it, they become “tagged” for a while. “Tagged” opponents are automatically chased by Ire and some other projectiles.

Almost all changes are recorded here:
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1whKCA5X8mkWbgZxPQcDMXIO6NU_D13W_mao7K1wTMOI/edit?usp=sharing

(BE SURE TO DELETE CHARACTER CACHE IN THE SETTINGS IF THE CHARACTER, or any modded character, SHOWS UP NULL!! Fixes the problem 95% of the time trust me.)

author: Catbox
title: Yharim, The God Seeker
description:
Yharim, Godseeker, Tyrant King, from the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2824688072]Calamity Mod[/url].

Developed by Catbox and officially endorsed by the Calamity Mod Team.
[i][url=https://ko-fi.com/catbox15993]Support Catbox on Ko-fi![/url][/i]

[h2]Install [url=steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3165815605]Character Codex Library[/url] or you will be missing features, including achievements and a unique unlockable.[/h2]

[url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3422501218]Official Style Collection available here.[/url]

[hr][/hr]
[h1] Current Ver: 1.3.1[/h1]
[hr][/hr]

Yharim is a high speed, limited mobility, brutal rushdown character. He amplifies his savage blows with both his fists and his menacing blade using Auric lightning to overwhelm opponents with offensive pressure and excessive damage.

In addition to the standard YOMI Hustle super meter, Yharim has [i]Auric Charges[/i].[list]
[*]Hitting combo count thresholds gives Auric Charge.
[*]Striking opponents who are blocking gives Auric Charge.
[*]Landing guard breaks gives Auric Charge.
[*]Yharim can convert super meter into Auric Charge using [i]Empower[/i].
[*]Yharim can normally store up to 3 Auric Charges. When [i]Tyrant's Might[/i] is active, he can store up to 5.[/list]

Yharim can consume Auric Charges either for mobility or to enable supercharged attacks with staggering lethality.

Yharim has two self-buffs [i]("installs")[/i] which overlap and can be used simultaneously:[list]
[*][i]Tyrant's Might[/i]: Requires 3 Auric Charges and 4 bars of super meter. [b]Permanently buffs Yharim[/b], making Auric Dash free, enabling his strongest moves, and empowering several other moves.
[*][i]Overcharge[/i]: Requires 5 Auric Charges and Tyrant's Might active. Temporarily enhances [b]all attacks[/b] to deliver aftershocks of red lightning on hit. Makes God Slaying Punch even more powerful.[/list]

All of this information and more is available in-game using the [url=steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3165815605]Character Codex Library[/url] mod.

[hr][/hr]

This mod features two fanmade Yharim themes composed by theforge129:[list]
[*][url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KBlDu3ytcrg]Install theme 1: Unnamed[/url]
[*][url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zSP1XaT-QEA]Install theme 2: Calamity before the Cynosure[/url][/list]

author: yanegeta
title: Zalgo...
description:
And he came in smoke and crackling shadows, and his fire was blacker than the abyss itself.
His voice split the heavens, tore flesh from bones, and none hid.
For he was the beginning of decay, and the end of time.
He put his rotten hand into the heart of the world and twisted the breath of life.
And from every sound his name spread, seven tongues, seven slaughters.
Children cried out to their mothers, but their mothers could not speak, for their lips were stuck together in pitch and blood.
Darkness crept from the edge of the world, and every shadow found a voice.
"He comes," they whispered, "He is already here. Zalgo with a thousand faces, bringer of misfortune."
And the world choked in his eye, for his eye was a hole through which the end flows.

author: Ace 0f Shades
title: Zessen
description:
Zessen is a hard-hitting punish character centered around conditioning the opponent to attack then cashing out with powerful counterattacks.

Some of Zessens attacks have a special window called Guardpoint where you can choose a frame to block either high or low (depending on the attack used) while attacking and cancel into special follow-ups on success. You may not always want to cancel into these follow-ups, however, as triggering a Guardpoint and following through with the original attack results in more damage than hitting normally.

His signature pressure move, Fuujin, is +2 on block and gives Zessen the opportunity to mix his opponent up with Shin, Nagiha, Issokutobi, and Rin, each requiring different counterplay. The plus frames make Zessen's Guardpoints even stronger as he can now use them to defend against faster moves like jabs.

Suigetsu no Hakobi grants access to empowered versions of Fuujin and Kou, but it can also be cancelled into Twirl. Twirl allows Zessen to gracefully dance through his opponent's attacks while approaching and then start a combo with an attack of his choice during their recovery. You can also cancel Suigetsu no Hakobi into Fuuga to store the charge if you have downtime.

Refined is a new super allowing Zessen to materialize a cloud of butterflies that can be controlled with the DI wheel. Standing in the cloud empowers all of his normals to spawn projectiles, along with enhancing some of his specials as well. The cloud has limited energy and is hard to slow down / turn around once it gets going, so you have to be smart with it.

[hr][/hr]
Note : This character is not completely finished and I'm still gonna add some more effects. Expect to see more particles and custom sounds in the future.
Shoutout to TriMay on the modding discord for rewriting my counter code and making it work better. Also shoutout to Trin for letting me use code from Shogi (even if I've since disabled it).

[h1]DO NOT USE ZESSEN WITH CHAT EMOJIS INSTALLED OR ELSE NINJA WILL BREAK[/h1]

[spoiler]Yes this character is just Anji Mito from Guilty Gear[/spoiler]

author: t*
title: Pūkeko BURST Replacement
description:
DAMNATION!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

REPLACES YOUR BURST WITH DAMN!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! (WITH SOUND!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!)
also known as Pūkeko in New Zealand, which is found in Indonesia, Papua New Guinea, New Zealand and Australia (fun fact).

[h3] works only with vanilla characters [/h3] because they're the only ones im willing to reskin.

[h3] IF YOU WANT TO MAKE ONE OF THESE FOR ANY CHARACTER YOU WANT: [/h3]
right click yomi on steam > browse local files > go back two folders (so steamapps) > workshop > content > 2212330 > 3472052098 > extract the .zip > overwrites folder > copy and paste literally any of the folders and rename it to your character*

then compress the full folder into a .zip file (should look like DAMNATION.zip, which contains a folder called DAMNATION, and inside it has an Overwrites folder and some other files)

author: Leftie
title: Acceleration of HUSTLE | Arena Gamemode
description:
[h1]NOT COMPATIBLE WITH DYNAMIC PLATFORMS! UNINSTALL IT OR ELSE THIS WILL NOT WORK CORRECTLY![/h1]

Inspired by [i]Acceleration of Suguri[/i], this zero-gravity gamemode places hustlers in a bubble arena with infinite air movements and pits them against one another in zoner heaven given shape. [b]Plays best with heavy projectile zoners, such as Astrologian, Foreigner, and Record Vainglory![/b]

All characters are given four gamemode-exclusive actions:
- [b]Accelerate[/b]: An XYPlot Air Dash equivalent to Ninja's Air Dash.
- [b]Weave[/b]: A stronger Accelerate which, in exchange for costing 1/4 of your Burst and being locked at maximum speed, gives complete projectile invulnerability and collision pass-through.
- [b]Basic Shot[/b]: A linear-moving bullet aimable via XYPlot, and can fire several in short sequence for half a bar of Super.
- [b]Homing Shot[/b]: A homing bullet that costs half a bar of Super, aimable via XYPlot, and can fire several in short sequence for an additional half-bar of Super.

[u]As with all gamemodes, your mileage will vary between modded characters. Some will not work properly and will need bugfixes or support from their original mod authors, [b]please don't cry to me about it![/b][/u]

[h1][u]Known issues:[/u][/h1]
- If Dynamic Platforms is installed, it prevents the injection of the gamemode-exclusive moves. This currently has no fix outside of uninstalling Dynamic Platforms.
- Ninja does not receive the gamemode-exclusive states. There is no known fix for this yet, but it is only known to happen with Ninja.

author: Leftie
title: Aikido | Arena Gamemode
description:
A lightning-quick CQC Arena inspired by Toribash's Aikido gamemode. 600 ticks, increased damage, and a small ring which stepping foot outside of means instant disqualification, this gamemode deviates from the long-term, setplay oriented default ruleset in exchange for a hectic rush to try and get one good touch before time expires, all while trying to pressure the opponent out of the arena.
(May not behave as expected with excessively large characters, such as HAG.)

[h1]Requires [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3302545730]Arena Loader[/url] to function. Play with [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3253671994]Toribash Sound Replacement Suite[/url] for the best experience![/h1]

author: uGuardian
title: MultiHustle
description:
Allows for more than 2 players
[b]Currently Singleplayer ONLY[/b]
(Online support is actively being worked on)

In singleplayer character select:
When selecting characters, you just keep clicking and the "P2" will become the next player, and you just press go when you're done adding characters.

In match:
Use the dropdown boxes at the top to select the current character, then the boxes below select the current opponent.

If things are broken, check the recent comments to see if I've already said I'm working on it, especially after a game update, since this mod is very touchy about core changes.

[strike]There is not and probably will never be an itch.io version of this mod, it modifies too much core code to reasonably maintain on outdated versions.[/strike]
Itch.io game version is unsupported but apparently works currently. I will not investigate bugs on the itch version.

Current known bugs:
[list]
[*]There is a known issue with loading replays with modded characters.
If you have trouble loading replays, try starting a singleplayer match with the used characters first before loading the replay.
[*][b]VUINE appears to be completely incompatible.[/b] I haven't checked into the specifics yet, but it appears to break multiple UI things, most importantly character lock ins.
[*][strike]If you press watch replay or undo while in match, it can cause issues with the character select. To fix this, just save the replay, go back to the main menu, and open it again.[/strike]
This might be fixed.
[*][strike]Predictions of simultaneous hits rarely end up being incorrect.[/strike]
This might be fixed.
[*][strike]Occasionally predictions appear to hit the wrong target.[/strike]
This might be fixed.
[*]Grabs are just buggy in general if they hit anyone who isn't the current primary target.
[*]Replays with modded characters will not load if you don't load up a singleplayer match first.
[*]Lethal Indicators mod just permanently displays "Lethal"
[*]Very specific sets of characters using vanilla characters cause intros to become interruptible.
[/list]

[h3]About online mode:[/h3]
There is a Discord server for the preview release of Online Mode. You can join it here.
https://discord.gg/3XPegc53bS

[h3]About Teams:[/h3]
The feature is in plans, but is only of medium priority and thus still hasn't been started on yet.

author: Fleig
title: Custom Stage Loader
description:
A tool that loads custom stages to the game, includes:

- A toggle to disable or enable the stage lines.
- A toggle for a random stage.
- The option to choose the active stage.

------------------------------------------------------------
Requires the Mod Options Library (soupModOptions):
https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2931722541&searchtext=
------------------------------------------------------------

Reminder that this is a community effort, thank you Liz for fixing a lot of my dumb code,
thank you Snazzah for being an amazing coder that helped a LOT with stage loader 1.5,
thank you supersonic for making mod options and for helping figure out how to implement
it on Custom Stage Loader, thanks Sul for brainstorming and helping on the development of
stage loader, thanks Scroomplers, for giving the mod idea and for making the first stage,
and thanks Ivy for helping this come true.

author: Leftie
title: Limber De Koko
description:
The stage tie-in for Quantum, inspired by a piece of album art from Tankakuka's [i]CENTIENCE[/i] album representing the song of the same name.

This stage has reactive elements! When Quantum is present, the background characters Kuka and Leeds disappear, and when either player hits half health, or when the match reaches half-time, a stage transformation occurs!

Leeds and Kuka, their likenesses, as well as [i]SOUL RING[/i] and the [i]CENTIENCE[/i] album, belong to Tankakuka. [url=https://twitter.com/TANKAKUKA]Give them lots of love![/url]
[h1][b][u][url=https://youtu.be/BWA3u0etQ48?si=rj1FNI7eR5EMhvFs]STREAM CENTIENCE![/url][/u][/b][/h1]

Ready to make the climb?

This stage pack was made for the OLYMPUS tournament qualifier matches, officially representing a direct aesthetic to the climb. Choose between Official, Radiant, Eclipse, or Minimal mountain views to accompany your journey in its brackets, or further beyond. Now, bearing the Mytikas Peak, taking an ethereal approach to the peak.

With its finale now passed, its champions beat with blood and gold.

Requires Stage Loader. Select the one you want to use through the Mod Options Menu for Stage Loader.

author: Fleig
title: Sneed's Seed and Feed (Formerly Chuck's)
description: The sign is a subtle joke. The shop is called "Sneed's Feed & Seed", where feed and seed both end in the sound "-eed", thus rhyming with the name of the owner, Sneed. The sign says that the shop was "Formerly Chuck's", implying that the two words beginning with "F" and "S" would have ended with "-uck", rhyming with "Chuck". So, when Chuck owned the shop, it would have been called "Chuck's Feeduck and Seeduck".

author: Forset Cabiri
title: YOMI Temple Stage
description:
"Your life is a hammer,
Your soul's a bullet.
Pray that your arc is beautiful.
Still your breath, little slug.
You must do what I could not."

---

Welcome, Pilgrim.
The eponymous Yomi Temple is playable NOW as a stage, available to any practitioner of the Nine Veils, regardless of your mastery.
Witness first-hand the chained battleground high above the troubles of the world. Dance across the mirror, feel the ripples cascade from your strikes, duel your nemeses on the edge of an eternal waterfall in this massive 3D stage.
When enough tension is wrought from the air, the massive foci of Dai-Moonben reacts, excitedly matching the combatant's bloodlust.
Don't think this is the last time you'll be here. We all are lashed to the Wheel, but you may have what it takes to break your opponent's will upon its spokes.

---

"Fix your gaze on the throne of heaven,
You're not getting my blood off your hands,
No matter how much you scrape the corpse."

---

(This stage may cause crashes with other mods that modify the render or projectile system in its current state)
(Requires Stage Loader)
(By ForsetCabiri and DesianSkies)

author: TVFLabs
title: AI Mod
description:
Adds a very rudimentary AI bot to play against. It automatically selects moves for P2, choosing a move and automatically DIing away from P1.
Doesn't work with CharLoader BUT it does work with the built-in version in the beta. Switch to charloader_beta if you want to use this alongside modded characters.
If anyone is curious about how it decides what move to use: It picks 10 random moves, simulates them all for 15 frames each, and chooses the one that does the most damage while leaving it with the most health. The reason it's not very smart is 1) it never changes the move data (aim, distance, direction, etc.), and 2) it has no way of seeing or predicting what you'll do.

author: Degritone
title: Keyboard UI Data
description:
Allows you to use wasd or the arrow keys to control XY plots and sliders. Hold shift to move faster, ctrl to go even [i]faster[/i], or both to go [i]really[/i] fast. You can also hold alt to enable reverse snap, making your keyboard inputs snap to the minimum distance from snapping to an angle/distance, rather than directly snapping to it.

You need to have your mouse hover the plot/slider you want to use your keyboard with, and some of them need you to click them first because ~reasons~.

Has Mod Options support, though it is not required.

author: KotlOfTheLight
title: Auto DI
description:
Are you new to the game?

Are you like me and forget to enable DI until you've taken half your health in damage?

Do you hate tome slap?

Then this mod is for you.  At the start of each turn, this mod will put your DI wheel opposite of your opponent's current position.
You can override this by manually making your own DI choice, but any DI is better than no DI in the event of ignorance or forgetfulness.
This has been tested online, vanilla and modded clients and no issues have been found so far.

You can also use game invites to invite other friends (although they must also have the mod installed).
Mod developers can also update the activity directly or add custom character images when you play them (if they add it to their mod)

This mod uses https://github.com/LennyPhoenix/GodotDiscordSDK for GDNative calls.
The library files should be automatically applied when you add the mod.

Although not required, you should use the Mod Options mod to change settings: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2931722541

If you need any help, you can ask me (Snazzah#0371) in https://discord.gg/yomimodding

author: Sthyerx
title: YOMI Random
description:
Adds a 'Random' button to the move select UI which will select a move at random.

Want to confuse your opponent? Never let them know your next move! After all, they can't know your next move if you don't even know it! Alternatively, you can hop into singleplayer and accurately recreate the experience of playing against a 3 year old that randomly clicks buttons.
Which ironically is probably the closest you'll get to a true singleplayer experience currently.

Currently the mod only picks a random available move, it does not randomize the options for the move (i.e. direction, distance, etc.). If there is is enough demand I'll consider adding it, since it will be surprisingly complicated to handle all the different possible options.

This mod mainly started as a side project for me for getting familiar with Godot and Yomi Hustle modding. I only tested the basic functionallities, so there may be some bugs. Feel free to report any you find.

This mod does not require the Mod Options Menu, but if you have it installed you'll have access to additional, toggleable features:
- Auto Lock In: Automatically locks in the selected move, after clicking the Random button
- Reset to Hold: If Auto Lock In is enabled, automatically reset the selected move to "Hold". This way you won't know which move was selected.

IMPORTANT: Other mods that make major changes to the UI or the game in general may conflict with this mod an will cause the "Random" button to not show up. Currently known conflicts:
- MultiHustle

If you find any other conflicts, let me know.

This mod will make it so you play doom instead of yomi hustle.
deadass just the freeware version of doom.

--- read before complaining ---

>this mod will make you unable to play normal yomi hustle<

this mod was tested with no other mods, if you are facing issues, either remove this mod and play normally  or remove all other mods to play this.

this mod is a bit heavy (40mb), sorry lmao

legal stuff about the mod is inside the zip of the mod.

--- controls ---

direction keys - front, back, look left, look right
alt - strafe mode (move left and right with arrow keys)
shift - run (suposedly)
ctrl - shoot
space - interact
enter - confirm
esc - go back
1 to 9 numerics - weapons

description:

author: Fleig
title: Tree
description:
This mod adds a new button to the in-game options.
The button will pop up a window with a tree.

Your goal is to join daily and water the tree, so it can grow.
If you miss a day, the tree will die.
Offline time still counts for the tree.

Once the tree is at the max growth, it will no longer die.

(you can optionally download Mod Options to reset your progress.)

author: Leftie
title: Yomidle | The Yomi Hustle Guessing Game!
description:
Introducing Yomidle, the Yomi HUSTLE guessing game! Try to guess the name of the move from context clues provided by previous guesses, and try to get it right in as few guesses as possible!
Includes full modded character support, customizable difficulty options and character filters, and tracked stats. See how high your streak can go!

Open the game from the Main Menu at the bottom of the screen, next to the version number.

Requires TriMay's Character Codex Library and Supersonic's Mod Options Menu.
